(33, 1, '2013-06-13 23:10:48', '2013-06-13 23:10:48', '<font SIZE="3"><blockquote>A girl should be two things: classy and fabulous"\n\n- Coco Chanel</font>\n\n<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/coco.jpeg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-63" alt="coco" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/coco.jpeg" width="224" height="224" /></a></blockquote>', 'Words To Preen By', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-girl-should', '', '', '2013-06-13 23:10:48', '2013-06-13 23:10:48', '', 0, 'http://preenme.wordpress.com/?p=2', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(34, 1, '2013-06-18 01:00:42', '2013-06-18 01:00:42', '<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/apply_lipstick.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image" id="i-24" alt="Image" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/apply_lipstick.jpg?w=415" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Does mom really know best? Why is it that our moms, grandmothers or that special maternal figure in our life always seemed to be effortlessly more glamorous than we could ever be? Despite the fact that there are thousands more beauty products on the market now, these amazing women always seemed so confident in their beauty routine.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">We asked our readers for their favorite beauty tip they learned from a special woman in their life. Here are our top ten:</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">1. "Do not neglect your eyebrows. They are the picture frame for your face. Don''t over pluck them no matter what the current style is or what your friends are doing."</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">2. "Apply your eyeshadow on with Q-tips because it''s easier and more sanitary than a brush."</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">3. So many of your moms love Vaseline! Put it around the eyes at night. Use it to take makeup off since soap can burn your eyes and can dry out your skin. Apply it on your lips, hands, elbows and feet at night.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">4. "Use a straight pin to separate your eyelashes. (But don''t poke your eyeball!)"</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">5. "Clean your face and neck with milk twice a week."</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">6. "Use frozen spoons for tired eyes/dark circles."</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">7. "My grandma, who was awesome, always wore red lipstick ...even if she didn''t wear much else on her face....always wear lipstick! And polka dots! She was my fashion idol!"</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">8. "My mother and grandmother always told us to walk like a lady. Head high, boobies enter the room first butt last."</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">9. "Use lotion to remove stubborn mascara."</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">10. "Years ago I went to London with a friend. We got off the plane, went to the bathroom to freshen up, I came out looking like I just got off a flight, she came out looking like she just woke  from a 12 hour nap. That’s when I learned to use blush."</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Now that we are sufficiently inspired, we''ve gone ahead and compiled a few of our favorite ''Mom Approved'' looks:</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Nothing screams ''Old Hollywood'' like <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/8569004" target="_blank">Classic Matte Red Lips:</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/8569004"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/Top Ten Mom Tips/matte-red-lips_look_9b6fbd72caca66debce8b2c89e4d262d_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Bring back 60s Glam with a <a style="font-style:inherit;line-height:1.625;" href="http://www.preen.me/look/15145235" target="_blank">Big Girly Hair Bun:</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15145235"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/Top Ten Mom Tips/60s-hair-bun-tutorial_look_5d6327decc61b6062184c0fe857ef40a_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Your Grandma will love <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15375005" target="_blank">this Perfect Red Manicure reminiscent of the Fashionable Forties:</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15375005"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/Top Ten Mom Tips/coraly-pink_look_6158b63727a0747ea27e70ef13d6a378_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Want to give your mom a little experimental (albeit shocking) make-up lesson? Show her this <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/12919011" target="_blank">modern twist on the 70''s ginormous, dark, false lash trend:\n</a></font> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/12919011"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/Top Ten Mom Tips/flower-girl_look_9c989c0f17e9a2cce9f19cd262639950_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em><a href="http://preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is the world''s leading social beauty platform. Find brand new looks, how to''s and video tutorials every single day. </em></font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em>Have your own great beauty looks to share? Upload them to <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> for your chance to be exposed to millions of people every week.</em></font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em></em><em>Find us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity?ref=hl">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/preendotme">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://plus.google.com/106829692334629302305">Google+</a>.</em></font>', 'Top 10 Beauty Tips We Learned from Our Moms.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mom-knows-best', '', '', '2013-06-18 01:00:42', '2013-06-18 01:00:42', '', 0, 'http://preenme.wordpress.com/?p=8', 0, 'post', '', 5),
(97, 1, '2013-06-13 17:00:46', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'TBD\n\n<div class=''visually_embed''>\n			<img class=''visually_embed_infographic'' src=''http://thumbnails.visually.netdna-cdn.com/beautys-benefits_5029100309d78_w587.jpg'' />\n			<div class=''visually_embed_bar''>\n				<span class=''visually_embed_cycle''><a href="http://visual.ly/beautys-benefits/?utm_source=visually_embed">Beauty''s Benefits infographic</a> </span>\n			</div>\n			<a id=''visually_embed_view_more'' target=''_blank'' href=''http://visual.ly/beautys-benefits?utm_source=visually_embed''></a>\n			\n			\n		</div>\n\nTBD', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-06-13 17:00:46', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=97', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(162, 1, '2013-06-20 06:00:03', '2013-06-20 06:00:03', '<img src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/africa_femmevoileeWeb.jpg" alt="null" />\n\n<font SIZE="3">Think you’ve tried everything? Think again. The <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> community comes from all ends of the earth – so we thought, who better to tell us what beautiful women use in far flung corners?</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Listen &amp; learn:</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">1.  Seeds from under a plant called yucca, in the Navajo culture women washed thier hair with it. Rich in Vitamins and minerals, plus helps with hair growth. Long hair is sacred symbol to the Navajo culture</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">2.  I don''t know if this is a cultural thing, but my Sicilian grandmother swore by Oil of Olay. Well, it''s just Olay now, but she used it every day, and her skin always looked beautiful.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">3.  After brushing your teeth. Gently brush your lips too. Great for an exfoliation. Free!! Lol. It makes your lips super soft. And your lipstick n gloss glides on so smoothly.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">4.  I''m Puerto Rican so we inherited a lot from everywhere ... coconut oil on the skin, avocado, mayonnaise or olive oil for the hair, garlic oil for strong nails and fish oil for all around health</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">5.  I use sugar to exfoliate my body in the shower once a week, use lotion immediately after. Use the inside of a banana peel, then rub that on my teeth to use as teeth whitener.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">6.  East Indian - Turmeric for face (lighten skin, exfoliate and slow down any facial hair growth); coconut or amla oil for hair strength volume and shine</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">7.  I use tea tree oil and apple cider vinegar as an astringent. My skin in so clear! I also use an egg mixed with apple cider vinegar after I dye my hair. Makes it very shiny and helps the color to last longer seeing I use manic panic.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">8.  Shea butter and coconut oil for my skin. And beer for my hair once a week.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">9.  My mum use to clean her face with calamasi (small version of lime in our country) wash it off with water then apply egg white to her face for at least 30 mins to an hour then washed if off with cold water or ice. She 68 now but many people mistaken her like late 40s or early 50s.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">10.  Almond oil for hair. Leave overnight. Hair is so silky and grows quicker</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">11.  Extra virgin olive oil in almost everything : face , hands , hair ...</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">12.  Warm Green Tea bags under my eyes for 3 minutes every Morning to remove dark circles</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Now if you want to get inspired to see what great skin, eyes &amp; hair look like, here you go:</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/2831023">Natural Makeup</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/1440680">Fernanda G</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/2831023"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/natural-makeup_look_853ba0711e45eac1a7178bf3c810cac8_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/2165036">Bad Romance</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/191269">Jolani J</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/3332152"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/bad-romance_look_64ac2591cfc7fe47472b6c989527c5b8_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/3332152">Red Lasting Lust</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/2621313">Sarah S</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/2165036"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/red-lasting-lust_look_82b5ee9e6d4ca99b0368489facd1486f_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/2165604">Fiery Ombre Hair</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/1730109">Julie M</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/2165604"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/fiery-ombre-hair_look_ecbd200d1145158465d50bec932a8d86_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em><a href="http://preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is the world''s leading social beauty platform. Find brand new looks, how to''s and video tutorials every single day. </em></font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em>Have your own great beauty looks to share? Upload them to <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> for your chance to be exposed to millions of people every week.</em></font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em></em><em>Find us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity?ref=hl">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/preendotme">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://plus.google.com/106829692334629302305">Google+</a>.</em></font>', 'Top Beauty Tips You’ve Never Heard of From Around the World', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'top-beauty-tips-youve-never-heard-of-from-around-the-world', '', '', '2013-06-20 06:00:03', '2013-06-20 06:00:03', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=162', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(178, 1, '2013-06-23 14:10:44', '2013-06-23 14:10:44', '<img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/Summer-beauty-essentials.jpg" width="300" height="215" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3">The fact that it’s hot and either really dry or grossly humid (which is worse? Pick your poison), doesn’t mean we should look as icky as we might feel.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><span style="font-style:inherit;line-height:1.625;">To help you on your quest for summer glamour, our <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> community has shared their top tips to avoid that traditional a summer meltdown.</span></font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">The ones we heard over &amp; over? Drink endless amounts of water, SPF (we beg you!), and ditch the foundation for a BB cream.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">And the other top tips were:</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· Boil green tea and when it cools put it in a spray bottle and spray when you’re sitting by the pool or on the beach, keeps your skin nice and hydrated.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· Detox! No foundation or even powder. A bit of paraben free sunscreen and a dash of rice starch to keep it shine free. Your natural color shows, and you don''t feel weighted down.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· I put my lotions and perfume or bodysprays in the frigde. When I get out of the cool shower I slather on cold lotion and spritz myself. Very refreshing!</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· Loose powder not pressed→won''t mke ur skin look so oily. Lip stain not lip gloss→heat thickens gloss so it feels pretty gross. Bronzer 4 all skin types 2 give U that summer glow.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· DONT WEAR MAKEUP.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· The hairspray keeps everything from running or beading from sweat. Works for me during the heat waves.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· Skin tones change in the summer, so change your makeup to compliment this. Go easy on bronzer as this can make you look too dewy/sweaty. Hydration is important as is sunblock. Keep those toe nails pretty, exfoliate and moisturise your feet. Also if you find that your shoes rub more in the summer, spray your feet with deodorant (not body spray) before you put your shoes on. If you find your hair becomes frizzy in the humidity rub tumble dryer sheets in a downward motion over your hair. It helps control frizz and takes the static out.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· Sun hats!! large floppy hats to protect your face and neck when outside. Also protect your hair with a good moisturizer shampoo/conditioner.</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">· Sticking to mascara. No other makeup unless it’s totally necessary!</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3">Now that you know how not to melt, here are some great summer looks to test drive. Be sure to click on the photos for how tos, products and other similar looks:</font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16571001">Shimmery Gold &amp; Turquoise Liner</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/1580484">Joanna D</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16571001"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/shimmery-gold-turquoise-liner_look_139c774d2eee2a424a35a54687e52160_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16497004">0'' Calorie Creamsicle Lippies!</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/1393973">Molly A</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16497004"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/0-calorie-creamsicle-lippies_look_1d23ade599001844bb9b01fb3249aacf_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15341001">Northern Lights</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/187001">Iliana S</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15341001"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/northern-lights_look_58b06c68ceb1dbb9fd74834a6b4fcad0_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16560011">Tropical Flower</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/9943001">Edyta M</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16560011"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/tropical-flower_look_328b5f4db5e10861ea45d37a95da8c1f_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15131002">Messy Bridal Updo</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/609004">Marjonelle M</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15131002"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/messy-bridal-updo_look_5647935c6766dad45421586a000814cb_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15377002">Lovin Summertime</a> by MUA <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/113027">Risa B</a></font>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15377002"><img alt="Test" src="http://baeabdf4f00f14bc8044-861690637d9f177cba2ceff8564527be.r6.cf1.rackcdn.com/lovin-summertime_look_b9f9e08cb8c3ac39a74abc8539799ca0_look.jpg" width="200" height="185" /></a>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em><a href="http://preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is the world''s leading social beauty platform. Find brand new looks, how tos and video tutorials every single day. </em></font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em>Have your own great beauty looks to share? Upload them to <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> for your chance to be exposed to millions of people every week.</em></font>\n\n<font SIZE="3"><em></em><em>Find us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity?ref=hl">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/preendotme">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://plus.google.com/106829692334629302305">Google+</a>.</em></font>', 'Top Tips to Avoid a Beauty Meltdown This Summer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open'