(842, 1, '2013-07-18 18:46:34', '2013-07-18 18:46:34', '<h5 style="text-align:left;" align="center"></h5>\n<h5 style="text-align:left;" align="center"><b style="font-size:2em;"><a href="http://preen.me"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-909" alt="Preen.Me" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/1001.png" width="594" height="314" /></a>Preen.Me Global Beauty Platform Engages Peer-to-Peer Community of Artists &amp; Enthusiasts</b></h5>\n<h4 style="text-align:left;" align="center"><b>First Year: 1.6M+ Facebook “Beauty Addicts” </b><b>Anniversary Kick Off: The Preen.Me Blog</b></h4>\n<p style="text-align:left;">Since going live in 2012, <a href="http://www.preen.me/" target="_blank"><b>Preen.Me</b></a> has quickly become one of the largest global beauty platforms, as well as a growing, influential, and completely viral community of beauty users. This month, Preen.Me expands its reach and its peer-to-peer beauty authority with the unveiling of the official <a href="http://blog.preen.me/" target="_blank"><b>Preen.Me Blog</b></a>. With access to a vast library of valuable content -- over 20,000 looks from Preen.Me’s 1.6 million fans and 5000+ makeup artist members -- the Blog is intended to be a creative space where the Preen.Me editors present timely stories that reflect popular content from the Preen.Me platform – trending user-generated makeup, hair and nail looks &amp; other interesting commentary.</p>\n“The Preen community of beauty addicts is passionate, creative and always looking to each other for more inspiration. We have thousands of looks – all timeless – that we thought deserved a second life with a slight editorial eye. The Preen.Me Blog is a natural extension of our platform,” said <b>CEO and co-founder Tamar Yaniv</b>. “We can create micro-stories in an editorial way – such as focusing on a trend or a lifestyle beauty issue like “tired eyes” or “wedding makeup” – but keep it 100% about the looks or how-to videos uploaded by our members. We want to maintain the faith and trust we’ve built over the past year, as we continue to grow the largest global beauty platform in the industry.”\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/exotic_looks/"><img alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/wild.png?w=300" width="285" height="232" /></a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/bridal_looks/"><img alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/bride.png?w=300" width="285" height="230" /></a>\n\n<b>The Preen.Me User</b>\n\nPreen.Me began as a Facebook page – <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity" target="_blank"><b>Beauty Addicts</b></a>. As the page grew in fans and posts became viral on a daily basis, Preen.Me launched its official website in June 2012. A snapshot of the Preen.Me platform today:\n<ul>\n	<li>Preen.Me is geographically focused on the U.S., with 81% of engagement coming from this market.</li>\n	<li>The Preen.Me platform engages 7-8 million monthly users across all channels, which is five to ten times higher than that of   many household names in the global beauty industry.</li>\n	<li>Facebook Beauty Addicts has over 1.6 million+ fans.</li>\n	<li>The majority of Facebook fans (82%) are in the desirable 18-44 year old age range.</li>\n	<li>On average, a Preen.Me post on Facebook receives almost 4,000 likes, nearly 400 shares, and reaches over 150,000 people.</li>\n</ul>\nMost recently, Preen.Me launched <b>satellite Facebook pages</b> dedicated to specific beauty themes in order to provide more targeted content around the users’ top beauty interests: Hairstyle Addicts, Nail Polish Addicts, Blue Eyed Beauties, Green Eyed Beauties, Brown Eyed Beauties, Wild Beauty, All Beauty Tutorials, and more to come. “The idea is to help users – whether they are seasoned artists or total newcomers looking for help – find the look that is most appealing or helpful or inspiring to them at any given moment,” said Yaniv. “With the introduction of these micro pages on Facebook, you can still explore and have fun, but in a more targeted and effective way. And the amazing part is that our engagement rates have jumped 25% on the micro pages. Consumers are enthusiastically sharing, liking and commenting. So it seems that we are on to something here.”\n\n<a href="http://preen.me"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-933" alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/numbers.png" width="594" height="80" /></a>\n\n[caption id="attachment_854" align="alignnone" width="594"]<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/preenme_pdf4graph2.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-854" alt="PreenMe_PDF4graph" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/preenme_pdf4graph2.jpg?w=594" width="594" height="177" /></a> Source: Facebook Pages[/caption]\n\n<b>Buying Beauty Products: The Preen.Me Way</b>\n\nWith its growing platform – website, Facebook pages, Twitter, Pinterest, Instagram, Tumblr, Google+ and now the official Blog -- Preen.Me aims to revolutionize the $60 billion U.S. beauty market into a modern marketplace, fueled by passionate users, who are most importantly, eager consumers. With this solid platform in place, Preen.Me has taken the first step in creating a better way to buy beauty, through peer recommendation, experience, and tutorials.\n\nPreen.Me is poised to become the leading destination for all things beauty, transforming how people shop for beauty products. Preen.Me’s ultimate goal is to offer its members personalized product recommendations based on crowdsourcing and the user’s social graph, creating a better, more holistic way to buy beauty. With a simple search through the Preen.Me content database – for say, mascara or cream blush – results will give members the ability to compare products at different price points and across brands, all in one place. The key: peer recommendations, personal experiences with the product, and in some cases, a how-to video showing the best way to wear it. The Preen.Me beauty product search provides everything necessary to make a confident purchase, and makes buying beauty fun and engaging.\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1520288/"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-937" title="Urban Decay Naked Palette on Preen.Me" alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/urban.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1117210/"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-936" title="L''Oreal Voluminous Smoldering Eyeliner on Preen.Me" alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/loreal.jpg?w=23" width="23" height="150" /></a><a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1002643/"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-935" title="Sephora''s Moonshadow Baked Palette on Preen.Me" alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/sephora.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1140296/"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-934" title="M.A.C Cosmetic Lipstick Chatterbox on Preen.Me" alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/mac.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a>\n\n<b>Partnerships</b>\n\nWithout compromising the community experience, Preen.Me plans to roll out a number of collaborations with select partners, which will provide value both to the brands and the users. Brands will have direct access to a large, highly engaged community, 100% of whom are passionate about beauty. Preen.Me’s advanced database will provide brands with unprecedented information regarding actual product usage, price sensitivity and more, enhancing their ability to connect with customers and new trends.\n\n<b>How to Join the Preen.Me Community</b>\n\nBeauty enthusiasts can join the Preen.Me community in a number of ways:\n<ul>\n	<li>Website: <a href="http://www.preen.me/" target="_blank">www.Preen.Me</a></li>\n	<li>Facebook: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity" target="_blank">https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity</a></li>\n	<li>Twitter: @preendotme</li>\n	<li>Instagram: <a href="http://instagram.com/preendotme" target="_blank">http://instagram.com/preendotme</a></li>\n	<li>Pinterest: <a href="http://pinterest.com/PreendotMe/" target="_blank">http://pinterest.com/PreendotMe/</a></li>\n	<li>Google+: <a href="http://gplus.to/preendotme" target="_blank">http://gplus.to/preendotme</a></li>\n	<li>#preenme</li>\n</ul>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/nails/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-929" alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/nail.png?w=300" width="291" height="233" /></a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/hair/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-930" alt="" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/hair1.png?w=300" width="291" height="236" /></a>\n\n<b>More about Preen.Me &amp; Founders</b>\n\n<b>Tamar Yaniv, CEO &amp; Co-Founder,</b> has more than<b> </b>a decade’s experience in the fast-paced digital business arena, where she served in various senior managerial and marketing roles (B2C Poker, Seeking Alpha), focusing on the online gaming industry. In these roles, she gained extensive specialized knowledge in the management of pure digital companies, as well as an in-depth understanding of managing global operations and marketing.\n\n<b>Haggai Klorman, COO &amp; Co-Founder, </b>has spent his career as a driver of operational and transactional deals in a wide range of fields including Oil &amp; Gas, Technology and Finance (US Tech Discovery, ICE Capital), operating in global business environments in key markets such as Europe, the Middle East, Russia, Africa and the US. For more than a decade, he has developed and been a part of executive teams at start-ups, as well as managed vertical teams in established companies.\n\nIn October 2012, Preen.Me received an $800,000 round of seed funding led by Genesis Partners. The round also saw participation from <a href="http://www.crunchbase.com/person/li-ka-shing" target="_blank">Li Ka-Shing’s</a> Horizons Ventures as well as individual investor Oren Zeev.', 'Latest News', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'latest-news', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:46:34', '2013-07-18 18:46:34', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?page_id=842', 0, 'page', '', 0),
