(951, 1, '2013-07-31 12:14:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<span style="color:#666666;font-family:''Trebuchet MS'', Trebuchet, Verdana, sans-serif;line-height:18px;background-color:#ffffff;"> <a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/candy-red-lips_look_70d8704ba199a810629d6e7b5b2f870a_look.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-959" alt="candy-red-lips_look_70d8704ba199a810629d6e7b5b2f870a_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/candy-red-lips_look_70d8704ba199a810629d6e7b5b2f870a_look.jpg?w=265" width="265" height="265" /></a><a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/red-velvet_look_8ebb0d20b73675f6c375be98f9182c00_look.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-961" alt="red-velvet_look_8ebb0d20b73675f6c375be98f9182c00_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/red-velvet_look_8ebb0d20b73675f6c375be98f9182c00_look.jpg?w=265" width="265" height="265" /></a></span>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Women have been adorning their lips for thousands of years. Archeologists often refer <a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/smokey-eyes-and-red-lips_look_8341730dfd86efa7369674d397a3ab38_look.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-963" alt="smokey-eyes-and-red-lips_look_8341730dfd86efa7369674d397a3ab38_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/smokey-eyes-and-red-lips_look_8341730dfd86efa7369674d397a3ab38_look.jpg?w=180" width="200" height="180" /></a>to the red lips of women (and sometimes men) found in ancient Egyptian art as "The Kiss of Death" because of the highly toxic nature of the ingredients used to create such bold colors. Cleopatra was known to crush up beetles and ants and spread them across her lips in order to tint them red. Queen Elizabeth I, who is famously known for her bright red lips and pale white face was said to have worn these cosmetics because she believed it would ward off death. Her hand maids even continued to apply her make up even days after she''d been dead believing that the make up might bring her back to life.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Red lipstick, obviously, cannot bring a dead person back to life but with out a doubt it can certainly put some life into a dead outfit</span><span style="font-size:medium;">.<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/ruby-slippers-glitter-lips_look_3eb0a432742079f2f601c8f11f0f1ec9_look.jpg"><img class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-960" alt="ruby-slippers-glitter-lips_look_3eb0a432742079f2f601c8f11f0f1ec9_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/ruby-slippers-glitter-lips_look_3eb0a432742079f2f601c8f11f0f1ec9_look.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Here are a few tips to achieve a beautiful, crimson pout.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">1. Choosing the correct shade for your skin tone is paramount to pulling off this look. First you need to decide if your undertones are warm based or cool based. To determine your undertones, look at the veins in your wrist. If the veins are more blue based you have a cool undertone and should choose a blue red. If your veins are green based you have a warm undertone and should steer more towards orange <a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/christmas-look_look_7b87b2dad5b5638f4867ef3b2560dd61_look.jpg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-965 alignleft" alt="christmas-look_look_7b87b2dad5b5638f4867ef3b2560dd61_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/christmas-look_look_7b87b2dad5b5638f4867ef3b2560dd61_look.jpg?w=180" width="180" height="180" /></a>reds. If you''re not sure what your undertone is, you can''t go wrong with a true red. It typically flatters most skin tones.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">2. You must line your lips. Red lipstick smears. Always line your lips prior to applying the lipstick to keep that red under control. Try lining your lips with a nude pencil, rather than trying to match the reds. Matching reds is nearly impossible. To ensure one smooth color throughout your lips, line with nude instead.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">3. Most women are familiar with the plight for long lasting lip color. <a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/glam-red-lip_look_db2191207549b19daaadf932f44c1abe_look.jpg"><img class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-958" alt="glam-red-lip_look_db2191207549b19daaadf932f44c1abe_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/glam-red-lip_look_db2191207549b19daaadf932f44c1abe_look.jpg?w=180" width="180" height="180" /></a>For extra wear time try applying your liner and lipstick first. </span><span style="font-size:medium;">Next, blot with tissue paper and apply a light dusting of face powder. Seal in color by applying your lipstick one more time and you''re done!</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">“Beauty, to me, is about being comfortable in your own skin. That, or a kick-ass red lipstick.” - Gwyneth Paltrow</span>\n\n<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/perfect-full-red-lips_look_71bc7358c3c3c6a198d83b7d596cd878_look.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-962" alt="perfect-full-red-lips_look_71bc7358c3c3c6a198d83b7d596cd878_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/perfect-full-red-lips_look_71bc7358c3c3c6a198d83b7d596cd878_look.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a>', 'Getting The Perfect Crimson Pout', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-07-31 12:14:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=951', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1011, 1, '2013-07-22 13:49:22', '2013-07-22 13:49:22', '<em><span style="font-size:medium;">By Preen.Me Contributor Kimberly M</span></em>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Moving to a new place in the summer means no worries about slipping comically on ice or not feeling your frozen toes getting smashed by dropped furniture--until later when they warm up and start throbbing. However, summer inevitably waits to strike <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/17284001"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-1016" alt="stay-matte-but-not-flat_look_1852230e7d1a7b8949628f3b0405099d_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/stay-matte-but-not-flat_look_1852230e7d1a7b8949628f3b0405099d_look.jpg?w=300" width="250" height="250" /></a>with a steaming hot vengeance on the day you plan to move, leaving you wondering what kind of sweaty, grungy animal you will most resemble at the end of the day--a bedraggled tomcat after a night of prowling the streets or a raccoon that fell in the creek while trying to wash his food?</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"> For many of us the problem with wearing less makeup isn''t the lack of cosmetics but the feeling of vulnerability that is associated with foregoing our usual makeup routine.\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/1011507"><img class="alignright  wp-image-1020" alt="5-strand-braid_look_d5815dad2705c5204528403c93e4c131_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/5-strand-braid_look_d5815dad2705c5204528403c93e4c131_look.jpg?w=300" width="250" height="250" /></a></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Below are our Top Five Moving Day cosmetic and hair care tips. Click on the photos for tutorials, similar looks and products. Also, be sure to check out our <a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/everyday_looks/">Everyday Looks</a> page!\n</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">1) Apply a <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/16352004/">foundation primer</a> to keep your liquid foundation from smearing. <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/2072514/">Primer</a> improves the overall appearance of skin and does not melt even when pores are cranking out the sweat and sebum. <span style="font-size:medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/6477076"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-1019" alt="barbie-girl-makeup_look_085534fc346df0c7b1d32b73d0916eea_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/barbie-girl-makeup_look_085534fc346df0c7b1d32b73d0916eea_look.jpg?w=300" width="250" height="250" /></a>High-quality primers contain antioxidants beneficial to your skin''s health as well as SPF ingredients to reduce UV ray damage. </span></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">2) Nix the heavy foundation for a lighter alternative such as a tinted moisturizer or a sheer foundation that allows your skin to breathe instead of gasping for air on moving day. If you feel like you have just dived into the pool and lost your swimsuit bikini top without your foundation, try brushing (not patting) some loose powder over areas of your face that need a bit more coverage. Be sure to check out<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16922002"> Ariel''s foundation and concealer video tutorial</a> to ensure a flawless look. </span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">3) Early in the summer and haven''t had a chance to tan? Apply bronzer to places where <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16837005"><img class="alignright  wp-image-1018" alt="for-all_look_f2c47a1cc55062e69da15fbbbda1583c_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/for-all_look_f2c47a1cc55062e69da15fbbbda1583c_look.jpg?w=300" width="250" height="250" /></a>the sun normally strikes your face--chin, forehead, nose and cheekbones. Don''t overdo it by deciding to make your whole face look like an overbaked potato skin. Bronzer is meant to be an enhancer, not a foundation. Also, <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/16566035/">the best</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/16650008/">bronzers</a> are those that offer a combination of varying shades of brown. Remember to dust a smidgen of bronzer on your ears, earlobes and neck, especially if you are wearing your hair up and away from your face. White ears contrasted by a bronze-tan face may get you more attention than you bargained for.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/1378980"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-1017" alt="natural-everyday-lips_look_7cd4435ffacceb719e7097d3f4151da7_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/natural-everyday-lips_look_7cd4435ffacceb719e7097d3f4151da7_look1.jpg?w=300" width="250" height="250" /></a>4) Instead of mascara, <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1403699/">put some vaseline</a> on your fingers and smooth the vaseline onto your eyelashes. <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/15253010/">Use a mascara comb</a> to separate the lashes. You can wear <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/10153005/">waterproof mascara</a> but since makeup advice for moving day emphasizes the "less is more" adage, coating your lashes with black, sticky mascara won''t look right when the rest of your face offers a more natural, "just-got-up-in-the-morning" look. Well, not that natural but you know what we mean!</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">5) <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/7936037/">Pink</a> or <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/15771006/">pale rose</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/19684001/">lip</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/19684001/">gloss</a> will keep your lips <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/16428041/">moist and soft</a> looking and can be applied discreetly all day long. Regardless of your <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1400578/">favorite lipstick''s</a> ingredients or quality, heat and humidity will cause lipstick to thin and pool in those tiny lip cracks that you are always trying to get rid of but can''t. Nothing is more unfashionable and unattractive than partially worn off lipstick.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>Tell us your hot weather moving day tips are in the comments section!</strong></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em><a href="http://preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is the world''s leading social beauty platform. Find brand new looks, how tos and video tutorials every single day.</em></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Have your own great beauty looks to share? Upload them to <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> for your chance to be exposed to millions of people every week.</em></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em></em><em>Find us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity?ref=hl">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/preendotme">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/114026381779272019938/posts">Google+</a>.</em></span>', 'Five Must-Have Tips For Moving Day', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'five-must-have-tips-for-moving-day', '', '', '2013-07-22 13:49:22', '2013-07-22 13:49:22', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=1011', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1053, 1, '2013-07-25 13:15:22', '2013-07-25 13:15:22', '<p><span style="font-size:medium;">You know those desert island scenarios where you have to pick just one product to take with you for the rest of your life? Yeah... nightmare...we know. Does "my entire makeup bag" count?</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">We <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity/posts/496651610406712">asked our Preen.Me community</a> if they could only have one product on a desert island, what would it be? Here''s a breakdown of how you answered:</span></p><p><a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/desertpie2.png"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-1134" alt="DESERTPIE" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/desertpie2.png?w=300" width="600" height="350" /></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">The Top Ten!</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">1) Shampoo: Because there is no way that sun is going to dry our <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/18435001">precious</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/13034002">locks</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/199694">out</a>.</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">2) Sunscreen: This one is especially for you <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/4722016">fair</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/17408004">skinned</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/18259036">maidens</a>. Always a good idea to get our UV protection on.</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">3) Foundation: The holy grail of beauty products, some say. Seriously, who can live without <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16922002">faux</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/16475012/">flawless</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/16475012/">skin</a>?</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">4) Toothpaste: Ok so we are not kissing anyone on that deserted island, but we will need to be prepared for when that handsome captain comes to our rescue.</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">5) Lipstick: Because who says there is no one to impress under that gorgeous full moon?</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">6) Soap: It keeps you smelling fresh, plus it treats stings, wounds and bites. Preen.Me fans are oh so </span><span style="font-size:medium;">practical and versatile!</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">7) Lip Gloss: <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/6202124">A</a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1771087/">must-have</a> to help maintain your fabulousness with one quick swipe of the finger. </span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">8) Eyeliner: You ladies just can''t live without your <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16862005">eyeliner</a>, and for good reason. It''s the secret to not looking tired and can even double as face paint. Y''know, in case you encounter any local tribes.</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">9) Moisturizer: An essential product bound to be useful after a day in the sun. Being the ingenious women that you are, many of you even suggested making your own coconut moisturizer. Even if it''s just us and the fishies, we do need to feel luxurious.</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">10) Mascara: We think everyone knows the importance of <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/18795014/">mascara</a> on a desert island, right? RIGHT????</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;">What beauty product is your desert island pick? Share with us in the comments section.</span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;"><em><a href="http://preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is the world''s leading social beauty platform. Find brand new looks, how tos and video tutorials every single day.</em></span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Have your own great beauty looks to share? Upload them to <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> for your chance to be exposed to millions of people every week.</em></span></p><p><span style="font-size:medium;"><em></em><em>Find us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity?ref=hl">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/preendotme">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/114026381779272019938/posts">Google+</a>.</em></span></p>', 'Your One And Only Desert Island Product!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'top-beauty-products-you-cannot-live-without', '', '', '2013-07-25 13:15:22', '2013-07-25 13:15:22', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=1053', 0, 'post', '', 1),
