(1235, 1, '2013-08-08 10:50:19', '2013-08-08 10:50:19', '<em><span style="font-size:medium;">By Preen.Me Contributor Ingrid C</span></em>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1610" align="alignleft" width="300"]<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/3383512"><img class=" wp-image-1610     " alt="http://www.preen.me/look/3383512" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/exotic-gold-brown-eyes_look_852a2e8fb2489df5a51a3b30d037367f_look.jpg?w=300" width="300" height="300" /></a> Exotic eyes by Selina C.[/caption]\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">A few years ago, my college roommate was about to marry her longtime love, and I was honored she asked me to be one of her bridesmaids. Now, we <em>were</em> roommates and had stayed in touch after graduation, so she knew about my makeup <em>habit</em> (hey, we’ve all got some kind of addiction, right?). She mentioned in the weeks leading up to the wedding that a few of the bridesmaids didn’t wear makeup often, so she contacted a professional makeup artist who agreed to do each person’s makeup for an unheard of $8 per person. Sounded like a great idea, but the other seven bridesmaids (who probably needed her service) didn’t take advantage of it, saying they were happy with their natural look. That was, of course, until I walked in--<em>all dolled up</em>.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">The dressing room scene was, in a word, frantic as the women crowded in front of the room’s only full-length mirror. Standing there with elegant gowns and updos, a few of my ‘natural women’ suddenly realized that in this epic “Clash Of The Looks”, the formal look was winning by a landslide. All of a sudden, out of nowhere, comes…<em>wait for it…</em>every shade of tinted lip gloss you can imagine. Clear, clear with a rose-colored tint, clear with a glittery shimmer. One stepped out of the clear, clear world with a shade of red that could only look good on the cover girl model (whose complexion, by the way, was at least three shades lighter than hers). Now, if we were sitting across the table having drinks, this is the part where four-letter words start flying out uncontrollably. However, I doubt the editor would appreciate that cleanup, so for now, just imagine the chaotic scene, then imagine we’re at dinner. To put it mildly, it was a <em>hot mess</em> on a sweltering July afternoon.</span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1544" align="alignright" width="240"]<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/14061116"><img class="wp-image-1544  " alt="Nails by Zuzka S." src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/french_look_b8fe0014382101d1e65e43591d09485f_look.jpg?w=300" width="240" height="240" /></a> French Nails by Zuzka S.[/caption]\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">As the casual observer and the only person in the room rockin’ a complete look, all the attention suddenly turned towards me. They agreed amongst themselves that I was a semi-professional and quickly assigned me the task of giving each of them an impromptu makeover (for free, I might add), using my makeup palette. Oh yeah, and they all wanted their makeup to look <strong><em>exactly </em></strong>like mine. And in case I didn’t mention it before, not one of them looked even remotely similar to me.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">I tried to quickly pick out their best features and highlight them, using the palette I had, all the while educating them on what to look for if they decided to experiment on their own. Here, I’m sharing with you the few tips I shared with them to create a simple, yet elegant look if you are a bridesmaid without much experience in makeup.</span>\n\n[caption id="attachment_1564" align="alignleft" width="150"]<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/16570017"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1564 " alt="Full look By Iris H." src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/classic-look_look_d39111b022a158454304a71fc51bf2ed_look.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a> Classic look By Iris H.[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1549" align="alignleft" width="150"]<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/17317005"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1549 " alt="Makeup by Tamanna R" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/magenta-champagne-glitter-eyes_look_310ade0f5bf35a16bff0d83ee7518c72_look.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a> Glitter eyes by Tamanna R[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1552" align="alignleft" width="150"]<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/18375002"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1552 " alt="Lipstick by Chiara" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/perfect-full-red-lips_look_71bc7358c3c3c6a198d83b7d596cd878_look.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a> Full red lips by Chiara[/caption]\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>Figure out your best feature. </strong>My eyes are clearly my best feature, and I have lots of fun experimenting with shadows. Which of your facial features receives the most compliments? This is a big clue for the area you should focus on most.</span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>Choose long-lasting makeup options. </strong>Wedding day festivities last for several hours; therefore, when applying eye makeup, be sure to start with a primer on your eyelid first (which will keep the look fresh and vibrant all day). Tender moments at a wedding can quickly bring on the waterworks; therefore, waterproof mascara is a must-have.</span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>The eyes have it. </strong>If your eyes are your best feature, choose elegant but neutral shades. You can often purchase a pre-packaged palette from a department or drugstore which feature complimentary shades. Do yourself a huge favor, though--buy yourself a separate blending brush and practice, practice, practice until your makeup is blended perfectly.</span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>Read my lips</strong>. While many believe that the shade of lipstick you choose reveals a great deal about your personality or mood, you’ll want to be careful about your bridal day selection. Warm tones such as brown, taupe, pale peach or mauve are generally more fitting for the sophisticated look you desire as a bridesmaid. If you opt for purple or pink, be sure they are very light shades. With lipstick, you will always want to use a lip liner no more than two shades darker than your lipstick, and you will want to blend it. Also, apply a complementary lip gloss over your lipstick; it adds both a finished look and an extra layer which helps the makeup stay on longer.</span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>Who says it’s wrong to be cheeky? </strong>If you have high cheekbones, you will definitely want to highlight them. Having two complementary shades of blush is great; that way, you can apply the lighter shade directly onto the cheekbone (blend, blend, blend!), then use the darker blush to create a subtle contrast underneath. Bronzers are also a girl’s best friend.</span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>Preparation Is Key. </strong>Hate to remind you, girls, but as a bridesmaid, you will need to spend as much time as you can supporting your friend on her big day. We generally know several months in advance (okay, so I’ve been in a few weddings already, gheesh!). Practice ahead of time so your makeup routine on wedding day is second nature. Not everyone is like me, who actually enjoys playing with makeup at the local department store. (I’m now on a first-name basis with the associates). However, there are some excellent tutorials on YouTube. Get the right brushes (it DOES make a difference) and practice until it’s perfect.</span></li>\n</ol>\n[caption id="attachment_1548" align="alignleft" width="150"]<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15301001"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1548 " alt="Makeup by Beata Laura R" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/bridal-exotic-makeup_look_3d083884d59d9552f9211a3fa8f5eb05_look.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a> Bridal Makeup by Beata[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1574" align="alignleft" width="150"]<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/1431378"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1574 " alt="Nails by Lissi C." src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/pretty-easy-cute_look_9a15b7a062effe50ce29a0cdca118404_look.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a> Pretty Nails by Lissi C.[/caption]\n\n[caption id="attachment_1577" align="alignleft" width="150"]<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/8118030"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1577 " alt="Liddia D.''s lipstick" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/bitten_look_a4c453b1c89444406275d68046798b72_look.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a> Lips by Liddia D.[/caption]\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Get inspired! Find tons of ideas and ''how tos'' at our <a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/bridal_looks/">Bridal Beauty Page</a>.</span>', 'Bridesmaids: Pulling Together Your Look for The Big Day', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bridesmaids-pulling-together-your-look-for-the-big-day', '', '', '2013-08-08 10:50:19', '2013-08-08 10:50:19', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=1235', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1237, 1, '2013-08-26 13:17:06', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p>Women have a wide variety of goals when they set out to put their make up on for the day. Some like to look as if they are not wearing make up, others go for a glam look, and still others strive for a romantic touch. But one of the most central parts of any look is the eyebrows. perhaps because they serve as a frame for the eyes, that can display a wide range of characteristics as can be noted in these looks from <a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/eyes/">Preen.me</a></p><p>While there are some who have eyebrows that fall in just the right place and are the perfect shade and shape for the person, others seem to have a mind of their own, and they are determined to make their own statement, regardless of the wishes of their owner.</p><h2>Reading Your Eyebrows</h2><p>Eyebrow reading is just one small part of Chinese face reading, which dates back to the time of Confucius, around 500 B.C. The idea is that certain facial characteristics can give clues to a person''s past, present , and future. The 12 Houses (areas of the face) lends insight into a person''s personality, relationships, intelligence, career, and overall health. Eyebrows are most prominently mentioned in the 6th house, Xiongdi Gong, or Sibling House. Eyebrows were said to have a strong effect on relationships. The most desirable was long, thick, and straight brows as they signified affection, calmness, and courage. Thin, pale, and low set eyebrows, or those with a scar hinted at physical or emotional torment.</p><h2>Shape, Position, and Fullness</h2><p>Max Fulfner, J.D. has applied face reading techniques in modern times, and has made several observations about eyebrows. He looks at the basic shape of  eyebrows; curved, straight, or angled, as well as the position of the brows, whether they are set high or low on the face.</p><p>Curved eyebrows imples that a person is focused on people, and are able to understand things better when they are explained in a way that shows how people are affected. Straight eyebrows indicated a preference for the practical, factual with much attention to technical details and little interference of emotions. Angled eyebrows can be found on those who like control over the situations in their lives. Being right about things is a high priority, and they are willing to put in the work to make certain that they are.</p><p>The position of the eyebrows can be either high or low. High brows are conducive to a discerning personality, the type that prefers to think things through and ponder before acting. Lower eyebrows indicate expressiveness and an eagerness to act quickly in order to accomplish goals.</p><p>The amount of hair matters too. Bushy eyebrows are thought to be a sign  of mental activity, or a non-stop thinker. Thin, pencil line, eyebrows show a preference to focus on one thing at a time. Those with thin eyebrows may be more sensitive about their appearance and  think that people are judging them to a greater extent than what they really are. Winged eyebrows, thick near the eye, growing thinner on the outside shows a knack for planning. Brows that are thin on the inside and thick on the outside are considered managerial. People with these eyebrows might be slow to begin a new project, but once it is underway they are committed to seeing it through.</p><h2><strong>To Match or not to Match?</strong></h2><p>Once you''ve figured out how to either embrace your eyebrow shape, position, and fullness -- or figured out how to bend them to your will deciding on whether to match your eyebrow color to your hair color is something you want to do, or if you are ready to go out into the world with light hair and dark eyebrows, or sport dark hair and light brows.</p><p>For most, matching brows is usually a safe bet. But not everyone is looking for safety. Dark eyebrows on those with light hair have been popular for years, even when there is a significant contrast, like with the hair and brows of Gwen Stefani.  The opposite, going light with eyebrows and dark with hair still has not caught on, which could have something to do with that dark eyebrow preference that goes back thousands of years.</p>', 'Eyebrows:What different looks say about you', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-08-26 13:17:06', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=1237', 0, 'post', '', 0),
