(1239, 1, '2013-08-18 15:18:04', '2013-08-18 15:18:04', '<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/tamarimages.jpeg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2015" alt="tamarimages" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/tamarimages.jpeg?w=100" width="100" height="150" /></a><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>By Preen.Me CEO Tamar Yaniv</em></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">It used to be that I’d earned the bags under my eyes, the greyish tint to my skin and the glazed over look in my eyes by having just a bit too much fun, for which I happily paid with little sleep and feisty hangovers. These days, those same lovely traits are caused by a very small human who rules my schedule and my sleep – or lack thereof. If they weren’t so cute, would we let them? Highly doubtful.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">It has been five sleep deprived weeks since I became a mom. Most of my life is spent between bottles and diapers, and most of the time I look the part. But when I’ve actually left the house (joy!), people seem to be shocked by how good I look (how shocked they are is only a bit offensive). Which made me realize that as the CEO of Preen.Me I’ve learned a few tips to look fresh faced when I’m anything but. So exhausted moms everywhere, listen up! This is your shortcut to faking it until you make it (to bed that is).</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">1) Concealer is your best friend. It’s no longer your husband or your BFF. Use liberally under the eyes, blend properly, and don’t forget the inside corner, where shadows tend to hide. After trying a million I use <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1124451/">MAC pro longwear concealer</a>. A bit drying, but it’s the best I’ve found and it makes a huge difference.</span> \n<div style="clear:both;width:100%;text-align:center;"><a title="MAC Concealer" href="http://www.preen.me/product/1124451/" target="_blank" rel="http://www.preen.me/product/1124451/"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-622" alt="MAC Concealer" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/macconc31pol0xtpbl.jpg?w=200" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">2) Your eyelids need a pick me up too. I use <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1116950/">MAC’s Painterly Paint Pot</a> on the eyelid. It’s a base that can be worn alone and effectively acts as a concealer. If you’re like me and have thin skin, with tiny veins that tend to show up on the eyelid, you’ll be surprised at the eye opening effect this has.</span> \n<div style="clear:both;width:100%;text-align:center;"><a title="MAC Painterly Pot" href="http://www.preen.me/product/1116950/" target="_blank" rel="http://www.preen.me/product/1116950/"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-622" alt="MAC Painterly Pot" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/21nnkslwvyl.jpg?w=200" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">3) Blush will immediately make you look happier and more awake, and it takes a few seconds to apply (bonus!). <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/6235241/">Milani Baked Blush in Rose Doro</a> will give you that perky flush you so desperately need. </span>\n<div style="clear:both;width:100%;text-align:center;"><a title="Blush" href="http://www.preen.me/product/6235241/" target="_blank" rel="http://www.preen.me/product/6235241/"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-622" alt="Blush" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/41roxh1x0wl.jpg?w=200" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">4) Mascara will open up your eyes, but apply only on your upper lashes. Doing your bottom lashes will accentuate those bags or shadows (not what we’re after); doing only the upper lashes will give the eyes a lifting effect. My favorite is <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1590379/">L''Oreal Telescopic.</a></span>\n<div style="clear:both;width:100%;text-align:center;"><a title="Mascara" href="http://www.preen.me/product/1590379/" target="_blank" rel="http://www.preen.me/product/1590379/"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-622" alt="Mascara" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/tele21j9nbpehul.jpg?w=200" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">5) A coral or orange lipstick is a quick pick me up that changes your look completely. It’s not as harsh as a red and tends to be universally flattering. My current go to is Nars Niagara, which also has great staying power. An honorable mention also goes to <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/10621001/">Maybelline Color Sensational Vivids in Electric Orange</a>.</span>\n<div style="clear:both;width:100%;text-align:center;"><a title="Plumper" href="http://www.preen.me/product/10621001/" target="_blank" rel="http://www.preen.me/product/10621001/"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-622" alt="Lipstick" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/419omleew2l.jpg?w=200" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">6) Do your eyebrows! This is another quicky that is very effective at “finishing” your face. <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1754227/">Anastasia Brow Wiz Brunette</a> will help you get a groomed look. </span>\n<div style="clear:both;width:100%;text-align:center;"><a title="Eyebrows" href="http://www.preen.me/product/1754227/" target="_blank" rel="http://www.preen.me/product/1754227/"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-656" alt="Eyebrow" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/21mu1e10ngl.jpg?w=200" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">7) And if some kind soul babysits for long enough to give you enough time to do your nails, use a good topcoat so that it doesn’t all go to waste next time you’re washing the bottles. I used <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/1026620/">Seche Vite</a> and am surprised to see no chips after 5 days.</span>\n<div style="clear:both;width:100%;text-align:center;"><a title="Topcoat" href="http://www.preen.me/product/1026620/" target="_blank" rel="http://www.preen.me/product/1026620/"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-656" alt="Topcoat" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/31mlybhcbyl.jpg?w=200" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Voila! You are a quick 5 minutes to compliments at what a glowing mom you are.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Now it’s your turn – what are your tips to fake it?</span>\n\n<em><span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>About the Author:</strong> Tamar Yaniv, CEO &amp; Co-Founder, has more than a decade’s experience in the fast-paced digital business arena, where she served in various senior managerial and marketing roles (B2C Poker, Seeking Alpha), focusing on the online gaming industry. In these roles, she gained extensive specialized knowledge in the management of pure digital companies, as well as an in-depth understanding of managing global operations and marketing.</span>\n</em>', 'Take it from the CEO: How To Not Look Like The Sleep Deprived Mom You Really Are', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'take-it-from-the-ceo-how-to-not-look-like-the-sleep-deprived-mom-you-really-are', '', '', '2013-08-18 15:18:04', '2013-08-18 15:18:04', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=1239', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1241, 1, '2013-09-30 13:33:24', '2013-09-30 13:33:24', '<h5 style="float:left;margin:10px;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/19994003/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></h5>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Anyone who has caught the Discovery Channel during a mating season special knows that Mother Nature loves to play up sex-linked traits with bright colors. Whether it’s the <a title="Most Colorful Monkey Butts" href="http://www.popsci.com/science/gallery/2013-04/most-colorful-monkey-butts?image=3" target="_blank">Macaque monkeys</a> with their bright red rears or Blue Footed Boobies with their webbed cerulean feet, evolution is clearly visually inclined. But are humans the same? Science has told us for years that men are more visual than women when it comes to arousal, but <a title="Erotic images elicit strong response from brain" href="http://news.wustl.edu/news/Pages/7319.aspx" target="_blank">new evidence suggests</a> that it’s women, not men, who are more responsive to observable stimuli, though they don’t always own up to it (most likely) on account of cultural attitudes and social pressures.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n<span style="font-size:medium;"> </span>\n<h1>So, when it comes to attracting the opposite sex, is color important?</h1>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Humans reveal their viability as partners in more subtle ways than do our fabulous primate cousins with their gloriously chromatic backsides, but we have our tell tale markers too. <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15252001" target="_blank">Flushed cheeks</a>, <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/26180005" target="_blank">oversized doll eyes</a>, <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/15708006" target="_blank">dewy lips</a>, these are just a few of the features we try to create or enhance with makeup believing they’ll attract better mates, both in the short and long term. It’s high time science gave us some firm answers on which routines are effective and which we should throw out with last year’s eye shadow.</span>\n<h5 style="float:right;margin:10px;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/7221079/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></h5>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">After some thorough prodding, Mother Nature has indeed provided some helpful suggestions on how to enhance female beauty for a more successful dating experience. Well, kind of. Here we go.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">\n</span>\n<h1>Importance of Beauty</h1>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">If women are just as, and possibly even more, visual than men, isn’t attraction based on appearances more superficial than previously suspected? After all, society has played up men’s “uncontrollable” wandering gaze as inherently biological for decades! Not necessarily. A lot of the visual cues that create feelings of attraction are gathered unconsciously, and they do relate to appearance. There are often obvious physical catalysts in addition to subtler ones. A few we’re all familiar with include body shape, appearance of health, and facial symmetry. But, within these broad categories are many nuances, such as waist-to-hip ratio and similarity of features.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Beauty is undeniably important to attraction, both the subliminal and discernable kind. Since men and women alike size up potential significant others from the moment their two sets of eyes meet—and that initial influence is visually based, if only for the briefest of moments—it’s important to present a display-quality model from the get-go. Empirical evidence proves those flashes of initial judgment can have long-term repercussions on romantic interactions.</span>\n<h1></h1>\n<h1>Beauty Is Not Everything, However</h1>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">There’s good news for ladies that feel like plain Janes: average facial features with better symmetry are preferable to the unique looks we see strutting down fashion show runways or voguing on covers of magazines. Angelina Jolie’s pouty lips and Julia Roberts’ toothy grin titillate on screen, but without Hollywood’s influence, men may turn from these A-Listers’ singular physiognomy in favor of the girl next door’s <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22394274" target="_blank">more recognizable visage</a>. That very same study also suggests breast size and BMI predilections are cultural, and vary from time period to time period, something Marilyn Monroe and Kate Moss can attest to.</span>\n<h5 style="float:left;margin:10px;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/1672095/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></h5>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Even women with slightly distorted faces, thick waists, and narrow hips need not hustle to the nearest humane society and start collecting cats. Clearly, men and women couple up in happy, loving, sexually exciting relationships in the face of asymmetry and less than classically attractive countenances. And, without a doubt, these couples would rate each other as charming, alluring, even beautiful. So, what gives?</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Attraction based on physical beauty alone is a fleeting thing. It may start the engines purring, but studies show that when shown a picture of their sweetheart, <a href="http://www.livescience.com/3818-love-powerful-sex-study-claims.html" target="_blank">brain scans of males in love</a> reveal activity in the romance regions (ventral tegmental area and nucleus accumbens), not the lusty one (hypothalamus). Though there is some overlap, the gooey affection center wins handily.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Additionally, perceived compatibility proves a stronger force for attachment than sexual passion, as we might have guessed.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">So, we’ve learned that beauty is important, but not too important, that personality, compatibility, and a sense of humor do, indeed, count for more than a thigh gap, and that it couldn’t hurt to emphasize facial symmetry as much as possible. Now, let’s take that information and apply it to our routines so we can snag that hottie with a strong jaw and a doctorate in linguistics we bumped into (intentionally) at the local coffee shop.</span>\n<h1></h1>\n<h1>Makeup for Women Versus Makeup For Men</h1>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Evidently, there is some disparity between what women think they should look like and what men are innately attracted to. If symmetry and average features rule, then it’s time to separate the high glamor cosmetics from the subtle natural enhancements. That doesn’t mean that ladies should stop scrawling <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/25482035" target="_blank">intricately detailed winged eyeline</a>r on their faces or toning down their nail art. Makeup is definitely for women as much as it is for men (perhaps more so), and it’s a respectable method of self-expression. Having said that, we should save the feats of creative color genius for girls’ night out and stick to something simple for <a title="Preen.Me Night Out Looks" href="http://www.preen.me/tag/night_out_looks/" target="_blank">date night</a>.</span>\n<h5 style="float:right;margin:8px;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/15189006/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></h5>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">A completely paint-free face may seem like an enticing option here, but chances are, even the boys who claim they want all-natural are likely basing their opinions on looks that require some inconspicuous touch-ups. Anyone who has gone out and about with naked skin and been asked repeatedly if she felt ok, or if she was tired is familiar with this unfortunate reality.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Evening out skin tone for a healthy glow, contouring the cheek bones or nose lightly for a more symmetrical layout, or applying clear mascara to frame the eyes are just a few examples of surreptitious improvements that are undetectable to the opposite gender. The silver lining, if that’s called for, is these <a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/everyday_looks/?FB=Blog" target="_blank">minor amendments</a> are quick and easy to perform, which may streamline many morning routines.</span>\n<h1></h1>\n<h1></h1>\n<h1>Real Life Tips For Man Hunting</h1>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">If the purpose of all this research is to find success when dating, it helps to have actionable advice on how to accomplish those goals. Here are a few great tips and tutorials on makeup that creates a girl-next-door glow without the heavy Spackle.</span>\n<h2><a title="Preen.Me Eye Looks" href="http://www.preen.me/tag/eyes/" target="_blank"><em>The Eyes</em></a></h2>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">The eyes are the windows to the soul, according to Billy Shakespeare, but they are also the best facial feature for showcasing femininity and heightening our sexual dimorphism. Exaggerating the size and shape of our peepers while practicing restraint with liquid liner is tough, but let’s start with color. Choosing a light brown eye pencil for fair skin and medium to dark brown for increasingly tanned tones will appear much more subtle than drawing on a thick streak of dramatic black. Smoky eyes look great in the low lights of a bar, but in the afternoon sun—or in the wee small hours of the morning—it’s less foxy and more road kill.</span>\n<h5 style="float:left;margin:8px;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/9808039/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></h5>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">This <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/9808039" target="_blank">delicate, feminine look</a> is lightweight but still enhancing. Toned down a bit, it’s perfect for every day, and the seven total steps make getting dressed up for special occasions, like date night with Dr. Linguist, a swift job. The light browns, pinks and beige shades are demure and flattering on fair to medium skin tones, but darker or olive complexions may want to play around a bit to find something more suitable; it may mean going just a shade or two darker in each category.</span>\n<h2><a title="Top Tips to Avoid a Beauty Meltdown This Summer" href="http://blog.preen.me/2013/06/23/top-tips-to-avoid-a-beauty-meltdown-this-summer/" target="_blank"><em>The Skin</em></a></h2>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">A <a href="http://www.cnn.com/2009/LIVING/personal/04/13/o.laws.of.sex.attraction/" target="_blank">healthy glow</a> is naturally apparent when we’re ovulating, ladies, and that’s when men find us most attractive. We can fake fertility with some foundation know-how and improve presumptions of our fitness in just a few minutes of dabbing on primer. A little rouge goes for miles too, so dust off that blush brush thoroughly before applying. We’re going for a blooming spring expression, not a post-marathon flush. Don’t forget to check the neckline for dramatic changes in tone that are a dead makeup giveaway.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Foundation application can be confusing; a tutorial, like this <a title="My Foundation Routine By Julie M" href="http://www.preen.me/look/15014005" target="_blank">helpful basics video</a>, can clarify some concepts that novices might not know. It’s important for us to play around with colors and techniques in order to find a system that’s not only flattering, but for which we develop a facility.</span>\n<h2><a title="Preen.Me Lips Looks" href="http://www.preen.me/tag/lips/" target="_blank"><em>The Lips</em></a></h2>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Painting on a kissable pout is probably the easiest task in the whole makeup oeuvre. But, sometimes the wrong color can mess up an otherwise gorgeous (that is, symmetrical and average) situation. The essential lesson of the day is natural. That means no slick, oil spill lip-gloss or seductive red glamorpuss stains. A neutral shade of peachy pink, fleshy tan, or even plain old tinted Chapstick can flush the lips enough for a pert display, and it takes mere seconds to swipe on.</span>\n<h5 style="float:right;margin:8px;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25210003/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></h5>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Chapped, flaky, and dry lips are a definite no-no. It’s possible to skip lip treatments altogether and just present a fresh mouth, but that maw better be healthy and inviting, or Mr. Alpha Male, with his superior genes and tight tush, won’t plant kisses on it anytime soon. We all experience dry, peeling skin from time to time, but fortunately all that’s needed is a quick scrub with a moist toothbrush and a dose of moisturizing balm. This is for the good of the human race, after all; think of the children!</span>\n<h2><em>The Scent</em></h2>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Pheromones are a controversial subject. Some scientists think they may still affect our choices in mates, others believe we’ve lost the ability to detect these chemical excretions. Regardless of which side of the argument most professors currently stand, we can all agree that smell is crucial to attraction on more than one level. Unconsciously, men distinguish <a href="http://www.livescience.com/553-woman-smells.html" target="_blank">when women are ovulating</a>, and women find traditionally masculine men more appealing when they’re at their most fertile. Attempting to replicate these trace experiences borders on extremely silly, but smelling nice for boys is something completely within reason.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">When choosing a scent, women sometimes mistakenly pick a heavy, flowery, or musky aroma that completely distorts or camouflages their natural bouquet. Since our organic (but freshly showered, please!) smells are imperative to attracting a mate with a similar but complementary immune system, selecting a fragrance with a light, clean vapor makes infinitely more sense. In fact, choosing unscented deodorant over the “sunshower electric rain” and  “lavender puppy kisses” that lady antiperspirant brands try to force on us is probably wise as well. Not only are we increasing our chances for coupling with a superior partner, we’re also minimizing our daily beauty performance. It’s a win-win.</span>\n<h2><em>Noted Male Turn-Offs</em></h2>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">We’ve covered the baiting tactics that reel in suitors by the dozens, whether they’re privy to the techniques or not, but it’s also imperative to cover the known turn-offs that alienate and repel potential admirers. High maintenance hygiene routines, extravagant makeup, and irregular facial features obviously populate this list, but what are some less obvious tics that drive men back into their man caves? Well, they go hand in hand with the alluring attributes; they just sit on the opposite end of the spectrum.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">One behavior that sends us all fleeing is desperation. Remember, as we play up our perfect symmetry and minimize our visually induced physical responses, it’s ever important to remain confident, independent, and individual. While speed dating is fun and settling down with the perfect man—who is generous, has kind eyes, and loves “Sex and the City” marathons—is a mostly healthy future goal, dwelling on obtaining a relationship is a waste of time and universally unattractive.\n</span>\n<h5 style="float:left;margin:8px;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25317107/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></h5>\n<span style="font-size:medium;"> Focusing that energy on self-improvement, education, or the acquisition of contouring skills may attract men who catch a whiff of our awesome fundamental superiority.</span>\n<h2><em>In The End...</em>.</h2>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Fancy monkeys need bright red butts to signal their readiness for mating, but humans have evolved to detect much subtler forms of biological fitness. Though science still struggles to explain many of the behaviors we consider instinctive (like texting our ex at 4 a.m. after a bender), a lot of the most puzzling physical responses have reasonable foundations in fertility, genetic compatibility, and chemical attraction. Whether we’re using this information to improve our chances of luring in an intimate partner or merely discovering some intriguing nuances of human interaction, it’s nice knowing there are sound explanations we can utilize to our advantage.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Ultimately, makeup does play a pivotal role in mating, as it enhances our facial features to appear more symmetrical, and it imitates the health and flush of ovulation. But, unlike the rainbow-hued body parts of mammals in the wild, the bipedal Homo sapiens present their willingness to couple up by accepting an invitation for a drink.</span>\n\n<a href="http://blog.preen.me/2013/07/08/top-makeup-products-that-boost-our-confidence/g" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2920" alt="wecandoitimages" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/wecandoitimages.jpeg?w=114" width="114" height="150" align="alignleft" /></a>\n<em><span style="font-size:medium;"> Want more beauty tips to lure in your next mate? Find the<a href="http://blog.preen.me/2013/07/08/top-makeup-products-that-boost-our-confidence/" target="_blank">Top Makeup Products To Boost Your Confidence</a>!</span></em>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em><a href="http://preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is the world''s leading social beauty platform. Find brand new looks, how tos and video tutorials every single day.</em></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Have your own great beauty looks to share? Upload them to <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> for your chance to be exposed to millions of people every week.</em></span>', 'Makeup and Sex: Investigating the Connection', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'makeup-and-sex-investigating-the-connection', '', '', '2013-09-30 13:33:24', '2013-09-30 13:33:24', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=1241', 0, 'post', '', 0);
