(2036, 1, '2013-10-08 13:43:47', '2013-10-08 13:43:47', '[caption id="attachment_3139" align="alignnone" width="580"]<img class="size-full wp-image-3139" alt="post_image" src="http://www.preenmeblog.bitnamiapp.com//wp-content/uploads/2013/10/post_image.jpg" width="580" height="365" /> Exotic eyes by Selina C.[/caption]\r\n<h2>How It All Began</h2>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">The Pinup can be traced back to as far back as 1890 in France when magazines and postcards featured erotic nude figures. These photos were extremely risque at the time and were secretly collected by United States Army or Marine Corps as they were not officially sanctioned by the government. Back in the US, this was a time when burlesque was flourishing and performers and actresses used photographic advertisements to promote themselves. It was also a time when women''s freedoms were being repressed and females who were overtly sexual had to worry about societal ramifications. Pinup girls began to express themselves in a completely different way and were finally able to instigate change all women now are enjoying. </span>\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24329008/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24934111/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Turn of the Century Pin Up Glamour</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">During the Depression, there was an increased focus on female nudity. Besides Burlesque performers, famous actresses'' photographs were copied and sold. They were increasingly considered sex symbols. Before the first World War, Fernande Barrey, (Miss Fernande) arguably the world''s first pinup, displayed her cleavage and even posed with visible full frontal nudity. Soldiers during the war kept her photos in their lockers which began a trend for future GIs who''s morale was compromised and had only their fantasies to hang onto.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/1151015/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/1414254/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Thirties</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">In the period between the two World Wars, Esquire magazine began publishing cartoons that pushed sexual boundaries. This started a trend in pinup art and in the mid 30''s, after the Great Depression, the fascination with the pinup began to develop as it was after a long period of economic hardship. Women were looking for new ways to express themselves and thus began the creation of the fashion and make-up trends that now define the pin-up look such as the <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/10131047" target="_blank">pin-curls</a>, <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24896095" target="_blank">classic red lips</a> and the <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24329008" target="_blank">cat-eye.</a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/14731002/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/18981001/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Coined!</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">Pin-ups still were not sanctioned by the government at the start of the 40s. In 1941, LIFE Magazine had coined the term ''Pinup'' in a special issue. It was an issue dedicated to National Defense at the start of the war and to raise morale and keep GIs spirits up, Dorothy Lamour became the first official pin-up girl ready to be ''pinned up'' to men''s lockers all over the globe.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/7634747/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/13305003/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Wartime Pin Ups</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">By the time World War II began, Pinups were out in the open and sanctioned by the government. Photos were finally allowed to be pinned to airline cockpits and even on the side of tanks and aircraft as mascots. Banks distributed calendars to millions of customers displayed with sexy and flirty Pinup images. But most importantly, Pinups represented hope and home for lonely soldiers. They would adorn sexy yet wholesome Pinups next to the driver of a tank. Rita Hayworth became a popular Pinup at this time and even one of the atomic bomb tests was named after her.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24312006/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25603009/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Modern Pin-Ups</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">In the past decade, more and more women have been inspired by the classic Pinup look. Television shows like Mad Men have brought burgeoning female sexuality into the spotlight and women like Dita Von Teese and Christina Hendricks are bringing back the pin curls and long lashes. There has also been a growing trend to photograph theatrical pinup shots for one''s partner, or even just for themselves. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/3380055/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/1061236/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>The Legend of the Pinup</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">Pinups have always been about much more than eliciting erotic arousal. Pinups exhibit control and were as powerful as weapons during wartime. They provided hope to vulnerable men during tough times. Pinups also represented women''s freedom of expression and embodied the idea that contemporary women weren''t afraid to be judged on their sexual or voyeuristic encounters. It also paid homage to the beauty of the curvy woman and eventually inspired artists from all over the world such as Alberto Vargas (Peru) and Hajime Sorayama (Japan) to create illustrations, comics and paintings that continue to inspire in this genre.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24526036/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/10131047/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><em>How To Get The Look</em></h2>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me" target="_blank">Preen.Me</a> is excited to be a part of this growing sub-genre and there are tons of looks to help you get a dose of theatrical femininity and class. Be sure to click on the photos on this page to find how tos and all of the products you need.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/22321005/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/6185400/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><a href="http://blog.preen.me/2013/09/30/makeup-and-sex-investigating-the-connection/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-3034" alt="navy-smoke_look_2bd2082d717f8e72111fa0316bba799c_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/10/navy-smoke_look_2bd2082d717f8e72111fa0316bba799c_look.jpg?w=150" width="70" height="70" /></a>Want more history about the origins of makeup? See our blogpost on the <a href="http://blog.preen.me/2013/09/30/makeup-and-sex-investigating-the-connection/" target="_blank">Connection between Makeup and Sex</a>!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><em><a href="http://preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is the world''s leading social beauty platform. Find brand new looks, how tos and video tutorials every single day.</em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><em>Have your own great beauty looks to share? Upload them to <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> for your chance to be exposed to millions of people every week.</em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><em></em><em>Find us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity?ref=hl">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/preendotme">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/114026381779272019938/posts">Google+</a>.</em></span>', 'Keeping Pinup Alive', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'keeping-pinup-alive', '', '', '2013-11-12 11:02:59', '2013-11-12 11:02:59', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=2036', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2081, 1, '2013-08-22 09:30:52', '2013-08-22 09:30:52', '<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/ck-one-music-lounge-lollapalooza-boland_ph_michael-bowles.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-2082" alt="ck-one-music-lounge-lollapalooza-boland_ph_michael-bowles" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/ck-one-music-lounge-lollapalooza-boland_ph_michael-bowles.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="210" /></a>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Yesterday we checked in with ck one color cosmetics insider and celebrity makeup artist Jodie Boland.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>All About Jodie</em></span>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">With 15+ years of experience at the top of her industry, Jodie Boland’s career spans the globe: from her native Australia to London, where she studied at the London School of Fashion- to New York where she’s currently based. She works regularly with A-listers like Naomi Watts, Kristin Wiig, Channing Tatum and Matt Damon, but it’s her recognizable style that emphasizes healthy skin and freshness that embodies the Calvin Klein image and made her the perfect fit for ck one color cosmetics.</span>\n\n<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/ck-one-music-lounge-lollapalooza-knapp_ph_michael-bowles.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-2083" alt="ck-one-music-lounge-lollapalooza-knapp_ph_michael-bowles" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/ck-one-music-lounge-lollapalooza-knapp_ph_michael-bowles.jpg?w=211" width="211" height="300" /></a>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Preen.Me shares Jodie’s beauty insights and customized looks created for celebs <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24242002">Eve</a>, <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24086003">Alexis Knapp</a> and <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24118002">Emily Sholes</a> at ck one color Music Lounge at Lollapalooza Chicago in August.</span> See their looks below!\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Jodie’s Advice for Preen.Me Makeup Artists</em></span>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">1. “Work hard, be honest and love what you do.”</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">2. “Everyday is different so stay open-minded and be ready to adapt accordingly.”</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">3. “Put yourself out there, take small jobs and work for free - even Jodie did it!”</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">4. “A good eye is essential. Follow the latest trends, shows and magazines. Jodie’s bible is <a href="www.style.com">style.com</a>. Jodi recommends checking 3 - 5 magazines regularly – ranging from Vogue to more commercial magazines. “</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">5. “Follow what you love and build relationships with the magazines, photographers and stylists. Keep track of what they’re doing each season and try to get connected with those you respect and want to work with. “</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">6. “Appreciate every day. Always be grateful, kind and thankful.”</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Spotlight on ck one color cosmetics</em></span>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Modern. Minimal. Sophisticated. Calvin Klein is known for its cutting edge designs, groundbreaking advertising and legendary perfumes; from Obsession to ck one. ck one color cosmetics provides a simplified approach to beauty that embraces individualism and invites self-exploration: look real, define yourself, add intensity.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Jodie’s Looks:</em></span>\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24086003"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-2086" alt="blue-eyed-girl-alexis-knapp_look_f3ee2df3bb0ca7b36f1b3678f09557a1_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/blue-eyed-girl-alexis-knapp_look_f3ee2df3bb0ca7b36f1b3678f09557a1_look.jpg?w=300" width="200" height="200" /></a>\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24086003">Jodie brought out Actress Alexis Knapp''s baby blues</a> using <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24189003/">ck one powder quad eyeshadow</a> and <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24308004/">navy liner</a> on her lower lashline.</span>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24242002"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-2085" alt="glam-rock-eve_look_f7aa58dc82417c919014002fb6f6d702_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/glam-rock-eve_look_f7aa58dc82417c919014002fb6f6d702_look.jpg?w=300" width="200" height="200" /></a>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Rapper Eve rocked a <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24242002">fresh-faced and glamorous look</a> with <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24316001/">plenty of blush</a> and pearlescent <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24075017/">skin illuminator</a>.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24118002"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-2084" alt="punk-princess-emily-sholes_look_0334c7b8e36b023e4572f7674f4a9098_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/punk-princess-emily-sholes_look_0334c7b8e36b023e4572f7674f4a9098_look.jpg?w=300" width="200" height="200" /></a>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Jodie dolled up singer Emily Sholes with a <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24118002">proper rock star look</a>, complimenting a sexy cat eye with cool orange-red lips.</span>\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Advice for all Beauty Lovers: Keep it Light.</em></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Most people don’t have time and/or want anything too heavy. For Jodie the ck one color cosmetics address these issues perfectly - multipurpose and light, the line allows you to enhance your individuality and features. For example, if you have great lips Jodie recommends the New ck one Shine Lipstick to add a pop of color.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">To focus on the eyes, the<a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24308004/"> ck one Double-Ended Eyeliner</a> is perfect. Place the lighter color in the corner and put the darker color around the eye, then blend it out to really bring out your eyes.</span>\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24308004/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2097" alt="foundation2245884" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/eyeliner2245832.jpeg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Jodie’s top 3 beauty tips to feel good and look your best:</em></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">• Look after yourself. Keep your skin clean.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">• Lashes and brows. Keep your eyebrows groomed and not too thin is important because it helps to shape the face. Curling your lashes and a touch of mascara will open your eyes instantly.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">• Light face, bright lip. Use a light face makeup to brighten and add a pop of color to the lip for a fun, easy look.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Jodie’s top 3 ck one color cosmetics pick:</em></span>\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24317001/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2097" alt="foundation2245884" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/foundation2245884.jpeg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a>\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24317001/">ck one 3-in-1 Face Make Up with SPF 8 Sunscreen</a>. “It’s incredible! It has SPF 8, a primer, serum and enough. It gives a beautiful finish but light so it’s easy to build up if you want more coverage.”</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24301005/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2097" alt="foundation2245884" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/illum2245926.jpeg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24301005/">ck one Skin Illuminator.</a> “I’m obsessed with the subtle pearlescent finish”.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24299002/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2097" alt="foundation2245884" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/mascara2245865.jpeg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me/product/24299002/">ck one Mascara.</a> “The twist top moves the bristles into a diagonal formation, giving you more product to play with.”</span>', 'Spotlight on ck one color cosmetics celebrity Make Up Artist Jodie Boland', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spotlight-on-jodie-boland-and-ck-one-color-cosmetics', '', '', '2013-08-22 09:30:52', '2013-08-22 09:30:52', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=2081', 0, 'post', '', 0),
