(2481, 1, '2013-09-18 08:34:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/littleblackdresscartoon.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2723" alt="littleblackdresscartoon" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/littleblackdresscartoon.jpg" width="71" height="103" /></a>\n\nThe “Little Black Dress” has become a timeless necessity for every woman, creating a blank canvas for opportunities of self-expression. From a sassy short number, to a long and luxurious gown, a black dress can be dressed up or even dressed down to suit any occasion and personal style. Our Preen.Me followers have left us many amazing comments about what they think suits a Little Black Dress best, therefore we have come up with 4 amazing looks that compliment that Little Black Dress based on your input!\n\nHopefully these glamorous looks can help inspire you to step outside of your comfort zone and turn your black dress into a desirable ensemble.\n\n<em><strong>Sexy and Stylish</strong></em> -  Ashley Melissa Bedoya said her favorite black dress inspired look consists of a "red lip and sparkly eye". Shimmering eye pigments paired with red-hot lips, soft romantic waves, and a simple but sexy sparkly French manicure is the perfect evening look to pair perfectly with our Cushnie Et Ochs “Picture Perfect Dress”. If this doesn''t scream sexy, I don’t know what does!\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24486007"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2693" alt="Cherry On Top" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/mel-s-cherry-on-top.jpg?w=300" width="107" height="107" /></a>   <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/22770008"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2695" alt="Glittery Nails" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/pallina-p-brides-glittery-nails.jpg?w=300" width="107" height="107" /></a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/3389213"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2694" alt="Romantic Curls" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/dada-u-romantic-curly-hair.jpg?w=300" width="132" height="109" /></a>  <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/25480282"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2486" alt="Glitter Smoky Eye" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/smokey-glitter-cut-crease_look_d0757b8481616413da79a29448a527d5_look.jpg?w=300" width="106" height="106" /></a><a href="http://www.renttherunway.com/shop/designers/cushnieetochs_dresses/pictureperfectdress"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2489" alt="Cushnie Et Ochs &quot;Picture Perfect Dress&quot;" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/ceo.png?w=160" width="89" height="167" /></a>\n\n<em><strong>Pin Up Perfection</strong></em> - This Pin-Up inspired look reflects exactly what Prudence Angulim says is her fave little black dress look. "A nude eye and thick eyeliner" adds great drama to the eyes while a simple bright pink popped lip takes the stage. We chose a soft braided updo in order to show off the sweetheart neckline of the Diane Von Furstenberg “Dark Roses Dress”, while pretty and pink nail polish adds a little flirty touch to any manicure.\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24228003"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2700" alt="Pro Cut Crease" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/marisa-v-pro-cut-crease.jpg?w=300" width="107" height="107" /> </a><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/12822007"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2701" alt="Princess Lips" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/janine-f-princess-lips.jpg?w=300" width="105" height="105" /></a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/17248016"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2702" alt="Wispy Halo" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/tina-l-wispy-halo-milkmaid.jpg?w=300" width="117" height="117" /></a>   <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/23534002"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2703" alt="Outono Inverno" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/chantel-l-outono-inverno.jpg?w=300" width="117" height="117" /></a><a href="http://www.renttherunway.com/shop/designers/dianevonfurstenberg_dresses/darkrosesdress"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2704" alt="Dark Roses Dress" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/dvf.png?w=156" width="94" height="178" /></a>\n\n<em><strong>Classy and Casual - </strong></em>Fall inspired, the Calvin Klein “Ramon Dress” is perfect for those cool and casual outings, where a natural and neutral look still keeps you feeling fabulous, without the fear of overdoing it. Stacey O’Neil Johston says "A pale eye with lots of mascara" is a great way to look fresh while keeping the focus on the dress. Pucker up with a natural style gradient lip, and add some volume to your hair by creating a cute and curly half updo. But wait! Don’t forget about your nails! A shimmery gold is the perfect finish to this classy and comfortable outfit.\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/25149009"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2708" alt="Everyday Makeup" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/natalia-j-everyday-makeup.jpg?w=300" width="108" height="108" /> </a><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/5653045"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2709" alt="NATURAL GRADIENT LIPS" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/kathryn-p-natural-gradient-lips.jpg?w=300" width="131" height="108" /></a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24571004"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2710" alt="CRISSCROSS UPDO" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/tina-l-crisscross-updo.jpg?w=300" width="108" height="108" /> </a><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/25444002"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2711" alt="HOLORIFIC" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/annie-c-holorific.jpg?w=300" width="108" height="108" /></a><a href="http://www.renttherunway.com/shop/designers/calvinkleincollection_dresses/ramondress"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2712" alt="Calvin Klein" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/ck.png?w=152" width="88" height="174" /></a>\n\n<em><strong>Daring and Dramatic</strong></em> - Okay ladies, It’s time to let your inner diva out. Be daring and dramatic while wearing Blumarine’s “You Are Dismissed Gown” to any formal event, and you will without a doubt be the talk of the town. With a dress so luxurious, your makeup needs to reflect that. Joli Laws says "A smokey eye and dark red lips" will create a bold and brave evening look, paving the way to a creative and adventurous hair style such as the pompadour with shaved sides look we found. Now, you are almost runway ready, just add some dark red raspberry tones and you can glam up your mani in an instant.\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/look/25785017"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2715" alt=" BLACK IS ALL YOU NEED" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/yumemi-s-black-is-all-you-need.jpg?w=300" width="108" height="108" /> </a><a href="http://www.preen.me/look/25603009"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2716" alt="FAL PINUP" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/fal-pinup.png" width="111" height="107" /></a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/164832"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2717" alt="POMPADOUR" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/taylorg-pompadour.jpg?w=300" width="130" height="106" /></a> <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/25402092"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2718" alt=" RASPBERRIES" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/georgianab-raspberries.jpg?w=300" width="108" height="108" /></a> <a href="http://www.renttherunway.com/shop/designers/blumarine_dresses/youaredismissedgown"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-2719" alt="Blumarine" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/bmyad.png?w=147" width="88" height="180" /></a>\n\n<strong>For more creative ways to dress up your own Little Black Dress, go to www.Preen.me for the latest products and trends!  </strong>\n\n<strong>See more fabulous dresses at <a href="http://www.renttherunway.com/">http://www.renttherunway.com</a> </strong>', 'You can never over-dresse or underdresse with a Little Black Dress', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-09-18 08:34:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=2481', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2492, 1, '2013-09-15 15:11:03', '2013-09-15 15:11:03', '<em><span style="font-size:medium;">By Preen.Me Contributor Kirstie</span></em>\n\n<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/tom-ford-men-skincare-grooming-cosmetica-masculina-corrector.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2501" alt="tom-ford-men-skincare-grooming-cosmetica-masculina-corrector" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/tom-ford-men-skincare-grooming-cosmetica-masculina-corrector.jpg?w=106" width="206" height="270" /></a>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">In the spirit of equality I believe all men should indeed be allowed to use beauty products, without anyone questioning their masculinity or letting out a cry of “beauty products are for girls!” Sadly, most guys are still nervous about being judged and this leads to the inevitable – men becoming secret beauty addicts and discreetly using their girlfriend’s cosmetics and facial potions.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">There is a way of dealing with this but it must be conducted with great tact and clever detective work. Chances are, if you outright accuse your man of snaffling your concealer or taking liberal doses of your expensive face cream, he’ll go on the defensive. Instead you need to build up a case with plenty of evidence, so he can’t lie. As soon as you’ve exposed him, take him out and spoil him with some male beauty products instead and help him get over his fears.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Without further ado, here are the top ten ways of exposing a sneaky beauty-thief boyfriend!</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>1. He has the Tide Line.</strong>\nBack when we were novice beauty users (think grade 9 and 10) we too were the victims of foundation tide lines. Now we’ve learned to blend, but I doubt our boyfriends have. Sneakily ask him to look up then assess his jaw for foundation lines.</span>\n<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/grooming.jpg"><img class="alignright  wp-image-2506" alt="grooming" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/grooming.jpg?w=150" width="240" height="140" /></a>\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>2. He’s Beautifully Fragrant.</strong>\nThe tell-tale signs of ladies shampoos, facial creams and bath gels are the fragrant floral smells. Your boyfriend may be able to put all your bottles back where they came from without a sign, but he can’t hide the fact he smells of French lavender.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>3. Cosmetics in His Nails.</strong>\nHe might have learned that concealer needs to be blended, but has he learned to get rid of the fingernail stains it can leave behind? I doubt it. Make like Sherlock and check them.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>4. He Spends Too Much Time in The Bathroom.</strong>\nBoys are infamous for complaining about how long women spend in the bathroom, but if you notice your man suddenly lingers in there a little longer than usual, you might want to double check your products afterwards.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>5. He has a Radiant, Glowing Complexion.</strong>\nYou’ve spent a lot of money trying to give yourself a pore-less, smooth and glowing face..I If you suddenly start to notice your man looks like he has been photo shopped, and yet his diet of greasy takeaways hasn’t changed, be suspicious.</span>\n<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/rby-manscaping-tweezing-eyebrows-mdn.jpg"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-2508" alt="rby-manscaping-tweezing-eyebrows-mdn" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/rby-manscaping-tweezing-eyebrows-mdn.jpg?w=150" width="190" height="190" /></a>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>6. He’s Suddenly a Beauty Expert</strong>\nYou’re out shopping for your monthly beauty essentials and then he announces “actually, I think you should go for a combination skin moisturiser…” He says it before he even knows what’s coming out of his mouth. Take note. </span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>7. Your Beauty Products are Mysteriously Being Used Up Twice As Fast.</strong>\nThis is an obvious one and it may be the warning sign of a male beauty addict.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>8. You’re Sure You Left That There.</strong>\nMake-up that was once in your bag now sits on the kitchen table. Exfoliators that once lived in the bathroom cabinet now wander around the bathtub. Well they probably didn’t grow legs.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>9. He’s got a Sunshine-less Glow.</strong>\nYour man seems to have developed a sun-kissed tan, but you’re very sure he lives in rainy Britain? It might be time to check your self-tan bottle before things get out of hand.</span>\n<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/shaving-0509-lg.jpg"><img class="alignright  wp-image-2509" alt="shaving-0509-lg" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/shaving-0509-lg.jpg?w=150" width="190" height="190" /></a></span>\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>10. He’s Become Obsessed with Mirrors.</strong>\nIf your boyfriend has become more obsessed with his reflection than your pet budgie, then he’s probably checking to make sure he’s covered his trail. Luckily, he doesn’t know you’re on to him yet.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Have you spotted any of the signs? What product do you think men would love to use, but are too shy to try? Tell us in the comments section.\n\n<strong><em><span style="font-size:medium;">About The Author:</strong></span> <span style="font-size:medium;">Kirstie is a fashion blogger at <a href="http://www.Yurei.co.uk">Yurei.co.uk</a>. You can find her on <a href="http://www.twitter.com/Pelliphant">Twitter</a> and on <a href="http://facebook.com/pages/yureiboutique">Facebook</a>. You can also see her amazing looks at her <a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/25844007">Preen.Me profile page</a>. </span></em>', '10 Ways To Tell Your Boyfriend is Using Your Beauty Products', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '10-ways-to-tell-your-boyfriend-is-using-your-beauty-products', '', '', '2013-09-15 15:11:03', '2013-09-15 15:11:03', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=2492', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2517, 1, '2013-09-24 11:32:52', '2013-09-24 11:32:52', '<span style="font-size:medium;"><em>By Preen.Me Contributor Valerie Latona</em></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">If you’ve been following the Spring 2014 fashion shows in NYC, you''ve noticed that nails—bright, colorful nails—were one of the hottest accessories. Not surprising. Nail polish is one of the easiest ways to make a fashion statement, no matter what the season, without spending thousands of dollars on a designer outfit.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">But here''s one of my pet peeves: Why in the world do nail polishes need to contain all these chemicals (toluene, formaldehyde, and phthalates namely). These, according to the <a href="http://safecosmetics.org/article.php?id=224">Campaign for Safe Cosmetics</a> are “known or suspected to cause cancer, reproductive harm, asthma, and other negative health effects”. And if you pooh-pooh these “suspected” health effects as just that, consider this: A California Department of Toxic Substances Control Report says, at the very least, this toxic trio is pretty definitively linked to <a href="http://www.businessweek.com/ap/2012-04/D9U2C4JO0.htm">birth defects</a>. I mean if you were to paint these on your nails once in your lifetime, I’d say don’t worry about these toxic chemicals. But women like us tend to paint our nails a lot more often than that, with many of us getting our nails done at least once a week. Over a lifetime, who knows what havoc those chemicals might wreak on our health!</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25343040/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/20409010/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">At first I thought “Maybe these chemicals are necessary to keep the polish on—and the color strong,” but after learning that top salon brand OPI rid their polishes of toluene and phthalates and never put formaldehyde in them, well, I started to wonder why other brands haven’t followed suit.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">But I’ve come to find that are other brands like OPI women should be using. Zoya is one—and is actually one of the favorites of designer Peter Som, who used this vegan brand at both his Fall/Winter 2013 and Spring/Summer 2014 shows. It has an amazing range of colors and is free of the top toxins. (Peter Som even left a trio of custom-designed Spring/Summer colors—encased in a velvet box no less—on every editor’s chair at the latest fashion shows; but anyone can buy the colors <a href="http://www.zoya.com/content/category/Peter-Som-NYFW-Spring-2014.html">here)</a>.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">But spring is a long way off: the hot color for fall? That classic deep, dark, oxblood red or Zoya''s Metallic Goldie (shown in <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/1028317">Double Gold Accent Nail</a> below)...pretty fabulous!</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/1028317/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25237099/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Other brands that say they’ve gotten rid of this toxic trio: Sally Hansen, Orly, Deborah Lippmann, Essie, and Butter London.</span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">But buyer beware: no U.S. government body regulates the labeling of products because they are not considered a “drug” or “medical device” (crazy if you ask me; maybe the FDA needs to get with the program and think beyond drugs and medical devices!). So my rule of thumb: if you need to wear polish (think: job interview, hot date, big presentation), try one of the brands mentioned here. If not, give your nails a breather and go polish free once in awhile. And if you’re pregnant, don’t chance it! And please, please do us all a favor: when the polish chips, take it off. There’s nothing worse for your image than walking around with chipped polish.</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/9805176/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/7194092/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">I’d love to hear your thoughts: do you worry about these chemicals when you’re using polish? If so, what polishes (and colors) do you love?</span>\n\n<em><span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>About the Author:</strong> Valerie Latona is a healthy living writer/editor/blogger. She’s the former editor in chief of Shape—and has worked as a beauty/health editor at Allure and Harper’s Bazaar, to name just a few. Her passion: healthy living and healthy beauty (because, as she says, “if it’s not good for you, then why use the product?”). Find her on <a href="https://twitter.com/vlatonaINSHAPE">Twitter</a>, <a href="http://www.pinterest.com/vlatona/">Pinterest</a>, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/valerielatona">Facebook</a>, and at her <a href="http://www.valerielatona.com">website</a> where you’ll find more blogs from her on beauty, health, fitness, food, and more.</span></em>', 'Sexy, Non-Toxic Nail Polishes Every Woman Should be Wearing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sexy-non-toxic-nail-polishes-every-woman-should-be-wearing', '', '', '2013-09-24 11:32:52', '2013-09-24 11:32:52', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=2517', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2519, 1, '2013-09-17 15:53:38', '2013-09-17 15:53:38', '<span style="font-size:medium;">This month <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.lancome-usa.com/">Lancôme</a> launched a special collaboration where the top US based Preen.Me makeup artists received a Lancôme eye trio that includes the brand new <a href="http://www.preen.me/product/25409012/">Lancôme Artliner 24H</a>. The Preen.Me artists have have been challenged to create their own unique looks using these products. So far, the enthusiasm has been contagious and tons of amazing beauty looks have been uploaded to Preen.Me! Here''s some Twitter and Instagram love:</span>\n\nhttps://twitter.com/preendotme/status/378250503408599040\n<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/instalove.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2735" alt="instalove" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/instalove.jpg?w=150" width="320" height="240" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Preen.Me artists received Lancome''s Artliner 24H in a variety of colors:</span>\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/product/25608063/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2621" alt="3605533169377_AMETHYST_ARTLINER24H" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/3605533169377_amethyst_artliner24h.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://www.preen.me/product/25409012/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2620" alt="3605533169193_COPPER_ARTLINER24H" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/3605533169193_copper_artliner24h.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a><a href="http://www.preen.me/product/25577038/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2619" alt="3605533168950_BLACK_ARTLINER24H" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/3605533168950_black_artliner24h.jpg?w=150" width="150" height="150" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><em><span style="font-size:large;"><em>Inside Lancôme Social Beauty</em></span></em></strong>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">For more on Lancôme''s beauty world view and on the new <a href="http://www.lancome-usa.com/Lanc%C3%B4me-Artliner-24H-Superstar/artliner,default,pg.html.#l24-prize">Artliner 24H in Paris Contest</a>, we sat down with Lancôme''s Director of Social Media &amp; Communications, Mimi Banks. Having worked for one of the leading luxury cosmetics brands in the world, the wonderful and savvy Mimi knows a thing or two about what it takes to create a great look.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>Preen.Me: What are the key attributes to a great look?</em></span></strong>\n<span style="font-size:medium;"> Mimi: We love the creativity and individuality that comes from artist contributions submitted through our social channels, but the general formula for selection and publication is a mix of greatness: Good Execution, Strong attention to Detail, On Trend but not Cluttered, With a Luxury Feel.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>PM: What’s Lancôme’s Fall Color Story?</em></span></strong>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">M: A French brand, Lancôme has its roots in Paris, the chicest city in the world. This fall, we invite every woman to embrace her own Parisian dream with our modern take on an iconic look. The Fall Lancôme collection focuses on classic luxurious products in daring new shades. I’m a huge fan of the deep lip and nail shades like: Purple Fiction, Black Sepia and Grey Lumiere.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>PM: Tell us a little about the Artliner 24H. What sets it apart from other felt liners in the market?</em></span></strong>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">M: Lancôme’s precision felt-tip applicator allows you to effortlessly create any look. From a classic black to a daring multi-hued look, color stays for 24 hours.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>PM: What are the on-trend looks using Artliner 24H?</em></span></strong>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">M: I think a twist on the classic is always fun and playful. The cat eye has a slick aesthetic when applied with a clean line, but bold color.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>PM: What''s your advice regarding nail art?</em></span></strong>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">M: Quality looks start with a good foundation. Make sure the nails are filed, shapely and the cuticles clean. I see a lot of overkill in nail art: over-designed, colors that clash or too many layers. In terms of trends looks, we love a great “Party Nail” – a classic manicure that has one well executed nail with design elements.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>PM: What''s your advice when shooting your looks?</em></span></strong>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">M: Be careful with backgrounds. Clean white or a simple background really elevates the look. A nail look shot on a shag rug or your computer key board can be very distracting.</span>\n\n<strong><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>PM: Tell us about your #24HinParis Contest.</em></span></strong>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">M: This is THE contest for all liner gurus. Here is the time to show off your creativity and makeup expertise using liquid liner! We are looking for liquid liner looks that are chic, fun, and whimsical and of course inspired by Artliner 24H. Be creative! Looks should be uploaded to Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram using <a title="#24HinParis" href="http://www.lancome-usa.com/Lanc%C3%B4me-Artliner-24H-Superstar/artliner,default,pg.html.#l24-artliner" target="_blank">#24HinParis</a> and will be judged by the Lancôme team and a lucky winner will win a trip for Paris with a friend. The contest only is only open to makeup artists residing in the US. We are excited to see looks from the Preen.Me community! </span>\n\n<strong><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>PM: Thanks, Mimi! It was a pleasure!</em></span></strong>\n\n<em><span style="font-size:medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is a platform for makeup, nail and hair artists to show case their work and get exposed to millions beauty addicts every week. <a href="http://www.preen.me/uploadlook/#/upload">Upload</a> your best beauty looks today!</span></em>\n\n<em><strong><span style="font-size:large;">Sample Look Submissions</span></strong></em>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Here are just some of the gorgeous creations our VIP Preen.Me MUAs submitted. Click to see the products they used and to save it to your Preen.Me profile (by clicking ''Would'').</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24840014/small" width="310" height="365"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24809873/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25359114/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>\n<iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25621031/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'Creating Looks the Lancôme Way', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'creating-looks-the-lancome-way', '', '', '2013-09-17 15:53:38', '2013-09-17 15:53:38', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=2519', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2750, 1, '2013-09-22 12:31:28', '2013-09-22 12:31:28', '<a href="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/renee-2013-09-18-at-11-57-12-am.png"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2755" alt="renee 2013-09-18 at 11.57.12 AM" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/renee-2013-09-18-at-11-57-12-am.png?w=150" width="100" height="109" /></a><span style="font-size:medium;"><em>By Preen.Me Contributor Renée Strauss</em></span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">There are few bigger beauty moments in a woman''s life more important than her wedding day. And when all eyes are going to be on you, not to mention a professional photographer snapping photos you''ll cherish for the rest of your life, you want to look your best. Here are my five essential beauty tips every bride should keep in mind on her big day. Click on <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a>''s top <a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/bridal_looks">Bridal looks</a> below for easy tutorials and to see the products you need. </span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>1) Do: Stick to Your Style. </strong>\nThe most important thing you can do beauty-wise on your wedding day is to just stay true to yourself. You don''t want Mr. Wonderful to wonder what happened to the woman he fell in love with as you walk down the aisle looking like a stranger! If you usually sport more of a natural look, stay natural on your wedding day, just add a bit more for photos: More blush, more mascara, and make your lips a bit more glossy. If you are a makeup lover, be a bit more glam: Layer on a pair of lashes, stroke on a bit more contour, brighten up the blush, and deepen the lips.</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24542010/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24173014/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>2) Do: Schedule a Trial Run.</strong>\nIf you hire a professional makeup artist—which I suggest doing—make sure to have a trial session so you can give your artist feedback on the look she creates for you. You want the artist to know your personal style and show you off at your personal best...the operative word is <em>your</em> best! If you don''t want certain elements like false lashes, airbrushed foundation, or a particular eyeshadow color, it''s better to let her know in advance, not right before you walk down the aisle.</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25038001/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24115005/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>3) Don''t: Go Overboard with a Spray Tan.</strong>\nWhile having a bit of color on your wedding day can be nice, you don''t want that color to rub off all over your white dress. If you must do a spray tan, make sure to do it a couple days before the wedding so the excess solution can wash off.</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24341021/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24446020/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>4) Don''t: Test Out New Products.</strong>\nI have a latex allergy and when I made a public appearance at a show in Canada (with ten thousand people in the audience!), the makeup artist used latex brushes on my face. Ten minutes into my performance my eyes began swelling and my throat began to close—it was sheer mind over matter that kept me from walking off stage. A wedding is a much more intimate setting and you can''t simply "hold it in" until it''s over because "over" can last all day! So, no new products the day of in case you have a reaction. And please tell your makeup artist about any allergies you might have.</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25018001/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/20813001/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><strong>5) Do: Stash a Mini-Makeup Bag.</strong>\nKeep lip gloss, eyelash glue and some mattifying powder in a little bag on your sweetheart table for touch ups and emergencies. You never know when you might need those little essentials and you''ll be glad to have them handy!</span>\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/16839007/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/23087004/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Want tons of Bridal Looks? Get inspiration at our <a href="http://www.preen.me/tag/bridal_looks">Bridal Page</a>. </span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Are you a soon-to-be Bridesmaid? <a href="http://blog.preen.me/2013/08/08/bridesmaids-pulling-together-your-look-for-the-big-day/">See how to pull it together for the big day</a>. </span>\n\n<span style="font-size:medium;"><em><strong>About The Author: </strong>Renée Strauss is one of the most sought after bridal experts and stylists. Through her hit TV show, Brides of Beverly Hills, and her popular Huffington Post blog, Renée Strauss has been able to connect with fans all across the country, as well as internationally. From being the go-to stylist for celebrities and trendsetting brides-to-be &amp; frequently being called upon by film, television, commercial and print productions for her expertise, she now lectures B2B around the world on the subjects of entrepreneurship &amp; leadership. Renée is the Luxury Wedding &amp; Lifestyle Ambassador for LWH Hotels world-wide &amp; BobaluBerries, a California corporation. You can find Renée on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/reneestraussbh?ref=hl">Facebook,</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/ReneeStraussBH">Twitter</a> and <a href="http://www.pinterest.com/reneestraussbh/boards/">Pinterest</a>.</em></span>', 'Top 5 Beauty Do''s and Don''ts on Your Wedding Day', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'top-beauty-dos-and-donts-on-your-wedding-day', '', '', '2013-09-22 12:31:28', '2013-09-22 12:31:28', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=2750', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2939, 1, '2013-10-02 12:52:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Preen.Me''s beauty community prides itself on being a tight knit international beauty community with make up artists from far flung corners of the globe who all manage to come together, support one another, lend our wonderful fans their favorite, tips, tricks and .\n\nBelow are the makeup artists from each country we and how they bring a bit of their homeland to us wiht every gorgeous look they create:\n\n<a href="http://www.preen.me/profile/16007001">Camila</a> hails from the land of sensuality and : Brazil. Her looks are always fun as she''s not afraid to use a number of colors on one look but manages to  \n\nItaly	11% Lherma Hidalgo Rubia, Kiko nail Giulia\n\nPoland\n\nAustralia\n\nDenmark\n\nBrazil \n\n', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-10-02 12:52:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=2939', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3054, 1, '2013-10-15 14:09:28', '2013-10-15 14:09:28', '<span style="font-size:medium;">No, you''re not wearing rose colored glasses! October is Breast Cancer Awareness Month, and every year pink ribbons are placed on the company''s cosmetics counters across the United States.</span>\n\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25144012/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25577009/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n&nbsp; \n&nbsp; \n<span style="font-size:medium;">Cosmetics and breast cancer awareness have a long history together. Back in 1994, the Senior CVP of Estee Lauder, Evelyn Lauder was also a member of the board of overseers at the Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center.</span> \n\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/3536312/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/596096/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n&nbsp;\n&nbsp; \n<span style="font-size:medium;">She popularized the pink ribbon as a symbol for awareness of breast cancer and personally raised millions of dollars to fund treatment, diagnosis and clinical research for a cure. Her leadership inspired other cosmetic companies to follow suit, and today we have an array of brands who now donate a portion of their sales to the breast cancer awareness cause.</span>  \n\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/7422031/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/18611591/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n&nbsp;\n&nbsp; \n<span style="font-size:medium;">Here''s just a few:  Every year, L''Oreal creates beautiful new palettes of color for its <a href="http://www.lorealcolorofhope.com" target="_blank">Color of Hope Collection</a>. They also donate 5 percent from the sale of each item to <a href="http://www.ocrf.org/" target="_blank">The Ovarian Cancer Research Fund</a>. With every sale of their <a href="http://www.totalbeauty.com/reviews/product/6429752/shiseido-luminizing-lip-gloss-in-pop-life" target="_blank">Luminizing Lip Gloss in Pop Life</a>, $22, Shiseido will donate $5 to <a href="http://www.cancerandcareers.org/en" target="_blank">Cancer and Careers</a>, a non-profit organization dedicated to supporting working women living with cancer. $2 from each tube of <a href="http://www.totalbeauty.com/reviews/product/6001845/jane-iredale-sugar-butter-lip-exfoliator" target="_blank">Jane Iredale Sugar &amp; Butter Lip Duo</a> (in Phoenix, a gorgeous pink shade) sold will be donated to Living Beyond Breast Cancer. </span> \n\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;">\n<iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/6225318/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/15321001/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n&nbsp;\n&nbsp; \n<span style="font-size:medium;">Discover all of these amazing looks from <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> and become Pretty in Pink to show your support for the campaign</span> \n\n<table border="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25359114/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n<td style="padding:0;">\n<iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/21804001/small" width="310" height="496"  frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n', 'Get Pretty In Pink! Beauty & The Support for Breast Cancer Awareness', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'get-pretty-in-pink-beauty-the-support-for-breast-cancer-awareness', '', '', '2013-10-15 14:09:28', '2013-10-15 14:09:28', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=3054', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(3129, 1, '2013-10-27 12:56:36', '2013-10-27 12:56:36', '<span style="font-size:medium;">I’m a bit of a germ phone, I have to admit. I sanitize (or wash) my hands after touching just about everything: door handles, elevator buttons (you wouldn’t believe how many germs exist on these!), money, other people’s hands…you name it. I also never, ever, ever wear bare feet in a locker or yoga room; I always have a pair of flip flops handy—and if I forget (as I did this morning), I wear socks…even in the gym shower.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size:medium;">I mean, really, I have good reason to do so: there are germs everywhere and if I can prevent myself from touching them, I’m less likely to get sick (or so I think) or worse yet, get some icky fungal infection or warts.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size:medium;">But—like so many other people—I rarely wash my makeup brushes. Beyond gross, yes, I 100% agree. My reasons for not doing so are valid (or so I tell myself): I’m busy—and I don’t use all my makeup brushes (I have many) all the time. I usually brush on a bit of blush (or powder) and go. Or I just swipe on some eye shadow here and there—with a shadow brush—when I need to add a bit of color. I mean how dirty can they really get? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Turns out…plenty.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size:medium;">Makeup brushes are filled with dust, dead skin cells, dirt—and bacteria. Oil from our skin, plus makeup left on brushes, creates an environment that’s the perfect breeding ground for bacteria. Leave all that on there for days, weeks, and months…and you won’t want to see what you’re layering on your skin.</span>\r\n\r\nThe worst that can happen? On the very surface, these bacteria can contribute to breakouts and skin rashes. But, when it comes to anything near the eyes, you can also develop bacterial conjunctivitis (aka pink eye). Not pretty.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size:medium;">How to stop this cycle: you’ve got to wash your makeup brushes once a week or once every two weeks at the very least. The easiest way to do it: take your brush immediately after using it (otherwise, you’ll forget), dab with a tiny bit of baby shampoo (that way, it won’t irritate your eyes or your skin), suds it up with warm water, rinse, and lay flat to dry. (After all, you wash your skin at least once a day…why not your makeup brushes?)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size:medium;">There are alcohol-based spray-on products that help disinfect your brushes; they’re easy to use but—and I’ve tried these—but the truth is you still need to rinse your brushes under warm water (and even some shampoo) to get rid of the residual makeup left over on the brush. \r\n\r\n<span style="font-size:medium;">After looking at bacteria growing in petri dishes (and on makeup brushes), I’ve become a convert. Not only did I give my makeup drawer a fall cleaning to narrow my brushes down to the ones that are essential (it simplifies my cleaning). I also gave them (plus my hair brushes, too) all a good washing—and plan to do so regularly. Because the alternative is, well, just plain disgusting!</span>\r\n\r\n', 'The Not-So-Pretty Reality of Your Makeup Bag', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-not-so-pretty-reality-of-your-makeup-bag', '', '', '2013-10-27 12:59:22', '2013-10-27 12:59:22', '', 0, 'http://blog.preen.me/?p=3129', 0, 'post', '', 0),
