(3140, 1, '2013-10-27 12:18:15', '2013-10-27 12:18:15', '<img src="http://www.preenmeblog.bitnamiapp.com//wp-content/uploads/2013/10/post_image.jpg" alt="post_image" width="580" height="365" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3139" />\r\n<h2>How It All Began</h2>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">The Pinup can be traced back to as far back as 1890 in France when magazines and postcards featured erotic nude figures. These photos were extremely risque at the time and were secretly collected by United States Army or Marine Corps as they were not officially sanctioned by the government. Back in the US, this was a time when burlesque was flourishing and performers and actresses used photographic advertisements to promote themselves. It was also a time when women''s freedoms were being repressed and females who were overtly sexual had to worry about societal ramifications. Pinup girls began to express themselves in a completely different way and were finally able to instigate change all women now are enjoying. </span>\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24329008/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24934111/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Turn of the Century Pin Up Glamour</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">During the Depression, there was an increased focus on female nudity. Besides Burlesque performers, famous actresses'' photographs were copied and sold. They were increasingly considered sex symbols. Before the first World War, Fernande Barrey, (Miss Fernande) arguably the world''s first pinup, displayed her cleavage and even posed with visible full frontal nudity. Soldiers during the war kept her photos in their lockers which began a trend for future GIs who''s morale was compromised and had only their fantasies to hang onto.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/1151015/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/1414254/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Thirties</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">In the period between the two World Wars, Esquire magazine began publishing cartoons that pushed sexual boundaries. This started a trend in pinup art and in the mid 30''s, after the Great Depression, the fascination with the pinup began to develop as it was after a long period of economic hardship. Women were looking for new ways to express themselves and thus began the creation of the fashion and make-up trends that now define the pin-up look such as the <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/10131047" target="_blank">pin-curls</a>, <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24896095" target="_blank">classic red lips</a> and the <a href="http://www.preen.me/look/24329008" target="_blank">cat-eye.</a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/14731002/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/18981001/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Coined!</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">Pin-ups still were not sanctioned by the government at the start of the 40s. In 1941, LIFE Magazine had coined the term ''Pinup'' in a special issue. It was an issue dedicated to National Defense at the start of the war and to raise morale and keep GIs spirits up, Dorothy Lamour became the first official pin-up girl ready to be ''pinned up'' to men''s lockers all over the globe.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/7634747/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/13305003/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Wartime Pin Ups</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">By the time World War II began, Pinups were out in the open and sanctioned by the government. Photos were finally allowed to be pinned to airline cockpits and even on the side of tanks and aircraft as mascots. Banks distributed calendars to millions of customers displayed with sexy and flirty Pinup images. But most importantly, Pinups represented hope and home for lonely soldiers. They would adorn sexy yet wholesome Pinups next to the driver of a tank. Rita Hayworth became a popular Pinup at this time and even one of the atomic bomb tests was named after her.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24312006/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/25603009/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>Modern Pin-Ups</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">In the past decade, more and more women have been inspired by the classic Pinup look. Television shows like Mad Men have brought burgeoning female sexuality into the spotlight and women like Dita Von Teese and Christina Hendricks are bringing back the pin curls and long lashes. There has also been a growing trend to photograph theatrical pinup shots for one''s partner, or even just for themselves. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/3380055/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/1061236/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<em>\r\n</em>\r\n<h2>The Legend of the Pinup</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em></em>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">Pinups have always been about much more than eliciting erotic arousal. Pinups exhibit control and were as powerful as weapons during wartime. They provided hope to vulnerable men during tough times. Pinups also represented women''s freedom of expression and embodied the idea that contemporary women weren''t afraid to be judged on their sexual or voyeuristic encounters. It also paid homage to the beauty of the curvy woman and eventually inspired artists from all over the world such as Alberto Vargas (Peru) and Hajime Sorayama (Japan) to create illustrations, comics and paintings that continue to inspire in this genre.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/24526036/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/10131047/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><em>How To Get The Look</em></h2>\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><a href="http://www.preen.me" target="_blank">Preen.Me</a> is excited to be a part of this growing sub-genre and there are tons of looks to help you get a dose of theatrical femininity and class. Be sure to click on the photos on this page to find how tos and all of the products you need.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/22321005/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n<td style="padding: 0;"><iframe src="http://www.preen.me/embed/look/6185400/small" height="496" width="310" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><a href="http://blog.preen.me/2013/09/30/makeup-and-sex-investigating-the-connection/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-3034" alt="navy-smoke_look_2bd2082d717f8e72111fa0316bba799c_look" src="http://preenme.files.wordpress.com/2013/10/navy-smoke_look_2bd2082d717f8e72111fa0316bba799c_look.jpg?w=150" width="70" height="70" /></a>Want more history about the origins of makeup? See our blogpost on the <a href="http://blog.preen.me/2013/09/30/makeup-and-sex-investigating-the-connection/" target="_blank">Connection between Makeup and Sex</a>!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><em><a href="http://preen.me">Preen.Me</a> is the world''s leading social beauty platform. Find brand new looks, how tos and video tutorials every single day.</em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><em>Have your own great beauty looks to share? Upload them to <a href="http://www.preen.me">Preen.Me</a> for your chance to be exposed to millions of people every week.</em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;"><em></em><em>Find us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeautyAddictsCommunity?ref=hl">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/preendotme">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/114026381779272019938/posts">Google+</a>.</em></span>', 'Keeping Pinup Alive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2036-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-27 12:18:15', '2013-10